{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775859502125,"sessionID":"ses_28686b59affeAylUCxRXkYiV1W","part":{"id":"prt_d797987d8001RXrSBrKbB44DP5","messageID":"msg_d79797d78001NRVIbhv2bR5Vjk","sessionID":"ses_28686b59affeAylUCxRXkYiV1W","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_7c3843b8e8ef4c92b70e1b2c","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-025/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-025/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-025 — MetadataService 与数据模型 — Design\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: TBD\n\n(End of file - total 5 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-025 — MetadataService 与数据模型 — Design\n\n## Overview\n\nTBD","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-025/design.md","time":{"start":1775859502110,"end":1775859502124}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775859503472,"sessionID":"ses_28686b59affeAylUCxRXkYiV1W","part":{"id":"prt_d79798cab0016yMMzloVDcjMtk","messageID":"msg_d79797d78001NRVIbhv2bR5Vjk","sessionID":"ses_28686b59affeAylUCxRXkYiV1W","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_a23a1d43f6834349836ff80b","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-025/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-025/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-025: MetadataService 与数据模型 — Delta Spec\n2: \n3: ## Context\n4: \n5: - **Module:** `cmd/cli`\n6: - **Language:** Python\n7: - **Size:** M\n8: - **Base specs:** `cli-toolkit/design.md`, `cli-toolkit/spec.md`\n9: \n10: ## Delta Requirements\n11: \n12: ### Requirement: AgentMetadata Pydantic model\n13: \n14: The system SHALL define `AgentMetadata` as a Pydantic `BaseModel` with typed fields, defaults, descriptions, and validators for language, build_mode, and port.\n15: \n16: #### Scenario: Construct with required fields only\n17: - **GIVEN** input `agent_name=\"test-agent\"` and `entrypoint=\"main.py\"`\n18: - **WHEN** `AgentMetadata(agent_name=\"test-agent\", entrypoint=\"main.py\")` is constructed\n19: - **THEN** the instance SHALL have defaults `language=\"python\"`, `port=8080`, `build_mode=\"local\"`, `requirements_file=\"requirements.txt\"`, `registry_url=\"\"`, `registry_username=\"\"`, `registry_password=\"\"`, and all `Optional` fields as `None`\n20: \n21: #### Scenario: Construct with all fields\n22: - **GIVEN** a complete dict of all `AgentMetadata` fields\n23: - **WHEN** `AgentMetadata(**fields)` is constructed\n24: - **THEN** the instance SHALL have all fields set to the provided values\n25: \n26: #### Scenario: Required field agent_name missing\n27: - **GIVEN** no `agent_name` is provided\n28: - **WHEN** `AgentMetadata(entrypoint=\"main.py\")` is constructed\n29: - **THEN** Pydantic SHALL raise `ValidationError` for missing required field `agent_name`\n30: \n31: #### Scenario: Required field entrypoint missing\n32: - **GIVEN** no `entrypoint` is provided\n33: - **WHEN** `AgentMetadata(agent_name=\"test\")` is constructed\n34: - **THEN** Pydantic SHALL raise `ValidationError` for missing required field `entrypoint`\n35: \n36: #### Scenario: validate_language normalizes case\n37: - **GIVEN** input `language=\"Python\"`\n38: - **WHEN** `AgentMetadata` is constructed\n39: - **THEN** the `validate_language` validator SHALL normalize to `\"python\"`\n40: \n41: #### Scenario: validate_language accepts java\n42: - **GIVEN** input `language=\"JAVA\"`\n43: - **WHEN** `AgentMetadata` is constructed\n44: - **THEN** the validator SHALL normalize to `\"java\"` and accept it\n45: \n46: #### Scenario: validate_language rejects unsupported language\n47: - **GIVEN** input `language=\"go\"`\n48: - **WHEN** `AgentMetadata` is constructed\n49: - **THEN** Pydantic SHALL raise `ValidationError` indicating only `['python', 'java']` are allowed\n50: \n51: #### Scenario: validate_build_mode normalizes case\n52: - **GIVEN** input `build_mode=\"Cloud\"`\n53: - **WHEN** `AgentMetadata` is constructed\n54: - **THEN** the `validate_build_mode` validator SHALL normalize to `\"cloud\"`\n55: \n56: #### Scenario: validate_build_mode rejects unsupported mode\n57: - **GIVEN** input `build_mode=\"hybrid\"`\n58: - **WHEN** `AgentMetadata` is constructed\n59: - **THEN** Pydantic SHALL raise `ValidationError` indicating only `['local', 'cloud']` are allowed\n60: \n61: #### Scenario: validate_port accepts valid range\n62: - **GIVEN** input `port=8080`\n63: - **WHEN** `AgentMetadata` is constructed\n64: - **THEN** the `validate_port` validator SHALL accept it (within `1..65535`)\n65: \n66: #### Scenario: validate_port accepts boundary minimum\n67: - **GIVEN** input `port=1`\n68: - **WHEN** `AgentMetadata` is constructed\n69: - **THEN** the validator SHALL accept it\n70: \n71: #### Scenario: validate_port accepts boundary maximum\n72: - **GIVEN** input `port=65535`\n73: - **WHEN** `AgentMetadata` is constructed\n74: - **THEN** the validator SHALL accept it\n75: \n76: #### Scenario: validate_port rejects zero\n77: - **GIVEN** input `port=0`\n78: - **WHEN** `AgentMetadata` is constructed\n79: - **THEN** Pydantic SHALL raise `ValidationError` for port below minimum `1`\n80: \n81: #### Scenario: validate_port rejects above maximum\n82: - **GIVEN** input `port=70000`\n83: - **WHEN** `AgentMetadata` is constructed\n84: - **THEN** Pydantic SHALL raise `ValidationError` for port above maximum `65535`\n85: \n86: #### Scenario: Optional fields default to None\n87: - **GIVEN** only required fields are provided\n88: - **WHEN** `AgentMetadata` is constructed\n89: - **THEN** fields `description`, `region`, `version`, `image`, `auth`, `agent_endpoint`, `workload_manager_url`, `router_url`, `readiness_probe_path`, `readiness_probe_port`, `agent_id`, `session_id`, `k8s_deployment` SHALL all be `None`\n90: \n91: ---\n92: \n93: ### Requirement: MetadataOptions dataclass\n94: \n95: The system SHALL define `MetadataOptions` as a dataclass with a `from_options` classmethod for dict-to-dataclass conversion, used to capture CLI override options.\n96: \n97: #### Scenario: from_options with full dict\n98: - **GIVEN** a dict `{\"agent_name\": \"my-agent\", \"language\": \"java\", \"port\": 9090, \"entrypoint\": \"mvn run\"}`\n99: - **WHEN** `MetadataOptions.from_options(options_dict)` is called\n100: - **THEN** the system SHALL return a `MetadataOptions` instance with those fields set and remaining fields at their defaults (`language='python'`, `port=8080`, `build_mode='local'`)\n101: \n102: #### Scenario: from_options with empty dict\n103: - **GIVEN** an empty dict `{}`\n104: - **WHEN** `MetadataOptions.from_options(options_dict)` is called\n105: - **THEN** the system SHALL return a `MetadataOptions` instance with all fields at defaults\n106: \n107: #### Scenario: from_options with unknown keys ignored\n108: - **GIVEN** a dict containing keys not in `MetadataOptions` fields (e.g., `{\"verbose\": True}`)\n109: - **WHEN** `MetadataOptions.from_options(options_dict)` is called\n110: - **THEN** the system SHALL ignore unknown keys and construct the instance with known fields only\n111: \n112: #### Scenario: from_options with partial overrides\n113: - **GIVEN** a dict `{\"description\": \"My agent\"}`\n114: - **WHEN** `MetadataOptions.from_options(options_dict)` is called\n115: - **THEN** only `description` SHALL be set; all other fields SHALL retain defaults\n116: \n117: ---\n118: \n119: ### Requirement: MetadataService.load_metadata\n120: \n121: The system SHALL load agent metadata from a workspace directory, trying `agent_metadata.yaml` first, then falling back to `agent.yaml` and `metadata.yaml`.\n122: \n123: #### Scenario: Load from primary file\n124: - **GIVEN** `{workspace}/agent_metadata.yaml` exists with valid YAML content\n125: - **WHEN** `MetadataService.load_metadata(workspace_path)` is called\n126: - **THEN** the system SHALL parse the YAML, construct an `AgentMetadata` instance via Pydantic validation, and return it\n127: \n128: #### Scenario: Fallback to agent.yaml\n129: - **GIVEN** `agent_metadata.yaml` does not exist but `{workspace}/agent.yaml` exists with valid content\n130: - **WHEN** `MetadataService.load_metadata(workspace_path)` is called\n131: - **THEN** the system SHALL load and parse `agent.yaml` and return the validated `AgentMetadata` instance\n132: \n133: #### Scenario: Fallback to metadata.yaml\n134: - **GIVEN** neither `agent_metadata.yaml` nor `agent.yaml` exists but `{workspace}/metadata.yaml` exists\n135: - **WHEN** `MetadataService.load_metadata(workspace_path)` is called\n136: - **THEN** the system SHALL load and parse `metadata.yaml` and return the validated `AgentMetadata` instance\n137: \n138: #### Scenario: No metadata file found returns defaults\n139: - **GIVEN** none of `agent_metadata.yaml`, `agent.yaml`, or `metadata.yaml` exist in the workspace\n140: - **WHEN** `MetadataService.load_metadata(workspace_path)` is called\n141: - **THEN** the system SHALL return a new `AgentMetadata` instance with all default values (required fields unset, so Pydantic defaults apply for fields with defaults)\n142: \n143: #### Scenario: Invalid YAML raises parse error\n144: - **GIVEN** a metadata file exists but contains malformed YAML (e.g., unbalanced brackets)\n145: - **WHEN** `MetadataService.load_metadata(workspace_path)` is called\n146: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise a `yaml.YAMLError` or equivalent parsing exception\n147: \n148: #### Scenario: Pydantic validation failure on load\n149: - **GIVEN** a metadata file contains `language: \"rust\"` (unsupported)\n150: - **WHEN** `MetadataService.load_metadata(workspace_path)` is called\n151: - **THEN** Pydantic SHALL raise a `ValidationError` from the `validate_language` validator\n152: \n153: #### Scenario: Verbose logging on load\n154: - **GIVEN** `MetadataService(verbose=True)`\n155: - **WHEN** `load_metadata` is called\n156: - **THEN** it SHALL log which metadata file was loaded (or that defaults were used)\n157: \n158: ---\n159: \n160: ### Requirement: MetadataService.save_metadata\n161: \n162: The system SHALL persist `AgentMetadata` to `{workspace}/agent_metadata.yaml` using specific YAML serialization settings.\n163: \n164: #### Scenario: Save with YAML formatting\n165: - **GIVEN** a valid `AgentMetadata` instance and an existing workspace directory\n166: - **WHEN** `MetadataService.save_metadata(workspace_path, metadata)` is called\n167: - **THEN** the file SHALL be written to `{workspace}/agent_metadata.yaml` using `yaml.dump` with `default_flow_style=False`, `indent=2`, `sort_keys=False`\n168: \n169: #### Scenario: Exclude None fields on save\n170: - **GIVEN** an `AgentMetadata` instance with optional fields set to `None` (e.g., `description=None`, `region=None`)\n171: - **WHEN** `MetadataService.save_metadata(workspace_path, metadata)` is called\n172: - **THEN** the YAML output SHALL exclude all `None` fields via `model_dump(exclude_none=True)`\n173: \n174: #### Scenario: Overwrite existing file\n175: - **GIVEN** `{workspace}/agent_metadata.yaml` already exists\n176: - **WHEN** `MetadataService.save_metadata(workspace_path, metadata)` is called\n177: - **THEN** the file SHALL be overwritten with the new content\n178: \n179: #### Scenario: Verbose logging on save\n180: - **GIVEN** `MetadataService(verbose=True)`\n181: - **WHEN** `save_metadata` is called\n182: - **THEN** it SHALL log the path where metadata was saved\n183: \n184: ---\n185: \n186: ### Requirement: MetadataService.update_metadata\n187: \n188: The system SHALL load existing metadata, apply field updates from a dict, save the result, and return the updated instance.\n189: \n190: #### Scenario: Update existing fields\n191: - **GIVEN** valid metadata exists in the workspace with `language: \"python\"` and `port: 8080`\n192: - **WHEN** `MetadataService.update_metadata(workspace_path, {\"language\": \"java\", \"port\": 9090})` is called\n193: - **THEN** the system SHALL load metadata, apply the updates, save the result, and return an `AgentMetadata` with `language=\"java\"` and `port=9090`\n194: \n195: #### Scenario: Update with new optional fields\n196: - **GIVEN** valid metadata exists without `description` set\n197: - **WHEN** `MetadataService.update_metadata(workspace_path, {\"description\": \"My agent\"})` is called\n198: - **THEN** the returned `AgentMetadata` SHALL have `description=\"My agent\"` and the file SHALL be updated\n199: \n200: #### Scenario: Update with invalid values rejects\n201: - **GIVEN** valid metadata exists\n202: - **WHEN** `MetadataService.update_metadata(workspace_path, {\"port\": 99999})` is called\n203: - **THEN** Pydantic SHALL raise a `ValidationError` from the `validate_port` validator and the file SHALL NOT be modified\n204: \n205: #### Scenario: Update with no existing metadata creates new\n206: - **GIVEN** no metadata file exists in the workspace\n207: - **WHEN** `MetadataService.update_metadata(workspace_path, {\"agent_name\": \"test\", \"entrypoint\": \"main.py\"})` is called\n208: - **THEN** the system SHALL create a new `AgentMetadata` with defaults, apply the updates, save it, and return the instance\n209: \n210: #### Scenario: Verbose logging on update\n211: - **GIVEN** `MetadataService(verbose=True)`\n212: - **WHEN** `update_metadata` is called\n213: - **THEN** it SHALL log which fields were updated\n214: \n215: ---\n216: \n217: ### Requirement: MetadataService.validate_workspace\n218: \n219: The system SHALL validate that a workspace path exists and is a directory, returning a boolean result.\n220: \n221: #### Scenario: Valid workspace directory\n222: - **GIVEN** `{workspace}` exists as a directory\n223: - **WHEN** `MetadataService.validate_workspace(workspace_path)` is called\n224: - **THEN** the system SHALL return `True`\n225: \n226: #### Scenario: Missing workspace directory\n227: - **GIVEN** `workspace_path` does not exist on the filesystem\n228: - **WHEN** `MetadataService.validate_workspace(workspace_path)` is called\n229: - **THEN** the system SHALL return `False`\n230: \n231: #### Scenario: Workspace is a file, not a directory\n232: - **GIVEN** `workspace_path` points to a regular file\n233: - **WHEN** `MetadataService.validate_workspace(workspace_path)` is called\n234: - **THEN** the system SHALL return `False`\n235: \n236: ---\n237: \n238: ### Requirement: MetadataService._validate_python_workspace\n239: \n240: The system SHALL validate that a Python workspace contains at least one `.py` file in the root directory.\n241: \n242: #### Scenario: Python files present\n243: - **GIVEN** the workspace root contains `main.py`\n244: - **WHEN** `MetadataService._validate_python_workspace(workspace_path, metadata)` is called\n245: - **THEN** the method SHALL complete without raising\n246: \n247: #### Scenario: Multiple Python files present\n248: - **GIVEN** the workspace root contains `main.py` and `utils.py`\n249: - **WHEN** `MetadataService._validate_python_workspace(workspace_path, metadata)` is called\n250: - **THEN** the method SHALL complete without raising\n251: \n252: #### Scenario: No Python files raises error\n253: - **GIVEN** the workspace root contains no `*.py` files\n254: - **WHEN** `MetadataService._validate_python_workspace(workspace_path, metadata)` is called\n255: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError(\"No Python files found in workspace\")`\n256: \n257: ---\n258: \n259: ### Requirement: MetadataService._validate_java_workspace\n260: \n261: The system SHALL validate that a Java workspace contains a `pom.xml` file.\n262: \n263: #### Scenario: pom.xml present\n264: - **GIVEN** `{workspace}/pom.xml` exists\n265: - **WHEN** `MetadataService._validate_java_workspace(workspace_path, metadata)` is called\n266: - **THEN** the method SHALL complete without raising\n267: \n268: #### Scenario: pom.xml missing raises error\n269: - **GIVEN** `{workspace}/pom.xml` does not exist\n270: - **WHEN** `MetadataService._validate_java_workspace(workspace_path, metadata)` is called\n271: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` with a message indicating `pom.xml` is required\n272: \n273: ---\n274: \n275: ### Requirement: Metadata file format\n276: \n277: The system SHALL use YAML as the serialization format for agent metadata with specific structural conventions.\n278: \n279: #### Scenario: YAML structure matches model fields\n280: - **GIVEN** an `AgentMetadata` with `agent_name=\"hello-agent\"`, `language=\"python\"`, `entrypoint=\"main.py\"`, `port=8080`\n281: - **WHEN** the metadata is saved to YAML\n282: - **THEN** the file SHALL contain keys `agent_name`, `language`, `entrypoint`, `port` with corresponding values and no `None` fields\n283: \n284: #### Scenario: Complex nested fields serialized\n285: - **GIVEN** an `AgentMetadata` with `image={\"url\": \"my.registry/agent:v1\"}` and `k8s_deployment={\"name\": \"hello-agent\", \"namespace\": \"default\"}`\n286: - **WHEN** the metadata is saved to YAML\n287: - **THEN** the YAML SHALL contain nested mappings for `image` and `k8s_deployment` with `indent=2`\n288: \n289: #### Scenario: Field order preserved\n290: - **GIVEN** an `AgentMetadata` instance\n291: - **WHEN** the metadata is saved to YAML\n292: - **THEN** the key order in the YAML SHALL match the model field definition order (due to `sort_keys=False`)\n293: \n294: #### Scenario: Round-trip load/save consistency\n295: - **GIVEN** a valid `AgentMetadata` instance saved to `agent_metadata.yaml`\n296: - **WHEN** the file is loaded back via `load_metadata`\n297: - **THEN** the reloaded instance SHALL have the same field values as the original (excluding `None` fields that were excluded on save)\n298: \n299: ## File changes\n300: \n301: | Action | File | Description |\n302: |--------|------|-------------|\n303: | Add/Modify | `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` | MetadataService class with load, save, update, validate operations |\n304: | Add/Modify | `agentcube/models/pack_models.py` | MetadataOptions dataclass with from_options classmethod |\n305: | Add/Modify | `agentcube/services/metadata_models.py` or inline | AgentMetadata Pydantic BaseModel with validators |\n306: | Add | `tests/services/test_metadata_service.py` | MetadataService unit tests |\n307: | Add | `tests/models/test_pack_models.py` | MetadataOptions and AgentMetadata unit tests |\n\n(End of file - total 307 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-025: MetadataService 与数据模型 — Delta Spec\n\n## Context\n\n- **Module:** `cmd/cli`\n- **Language:** Python\n- **Size:** M\n- **Base specs:** `cli-toolkit/design.md`, `cli-toolkit/spec.md`\n\n## Delta Requirements\n\n### Requirement: AgentMetadata Pydantic model\n\nThe system SHALL define `AgentMetadata` as a Pydantic `BaseModel` with typed fields, defaults, descriptions, and validators for language, build_mode, and port.\n\n#### Scenario: Construct with required fields only\n- **GIVEN** input `agent_name=\"test-agent\"` and `entrypoint=\"main.py\"`\n- **WHEN** `AgentMetadata(agent_name=\"test-agent\", entrypoint=\"main.py\")` is constructed\n- **THEN** the instance SHALL have defaults `language=\"python\"`, `port=8080`, `build_mode=\"local\"`, `requirements_file=\"requirements.txt\"`, `registry_url=\"\"`, `registry_username=\"\"`, `registry_password=\"\"`, and all `Optional` fields as `None`\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-025/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775859503460,"end":1775859503470}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775859504835,"sessionID":"ses_28686b59affeAylUCxRXkYiV1W","part":{"id":"prt_d797991f4001VEAdUwObpmIOTD","messageID":"msg_d79797d78001NRVIbhv2bR5Vjk","sessionID":"ses_28686b59affeAylUCxRXkYiV1W","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_a3c0b5add0624aee9f23e603","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-025/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-025/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-025 — MetadataService 与数据模型\n2: \n3: **Module:** cmd/cli\n4: **Language:** Python\n5: **Size:** M\n6: \n7: ## 目的\n8: \n9: 为 AgentCube CLI 实现元数据服务层与核心数据模型，提供 workspace 元数据的加载、保存、验证和更新能力，支撑 `pack`、`build`、`publish`、`invoke`、`status` 全生命周期的元数据管理。\n10: \n11: 当前 CLI 各 Runtime 类需要读写 workspace 中的 agent 配置信息，但缺乏统一的服务抽象和强类型数据模型。本 AR 在 `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` 中实现 `MetadataService` 类，在 `agentcube/models/pack_models.py` 中定义 `MetadataOptions` dataclass，并使用 Pydantic `BaseModel` 定义 `AgentMetadata` 模型。\n12: \n13: ## 范围\n14: \n15: ### 包含\n16: \n17: 1. **`AgentMetadata` Pydantic 模型**\n18:    - 定义在 `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`（或独立模块）\n19:    - 22 个字段覆盖 agent 名称、语言、入口、端口、构建模式、镜像、认证、端点、探针、K8s 部署等\n20:    - 3 个 validators：`validate_language`（python/java）、`validate_build_mode`（local/cloud）、`validate_port`（1-65535）\n21:    - 支持 `model_dump(exclude_none=True)` 用于 YAML 序列化\n22: \n23: 2. **`MetadataOptions` Dataclass**\n24:    - 定义在 `agentcube/models/pack_models.py`\n25:    - 14 个可选字段，接收 CLI 命令行选项\n26:    - `from_options(cls, options: Dict[str, Any])` 类方法从字典构造\n27: \n28: 3. **`MetadataService` 类实现**\n29:    - `load_metadata(workspace_path)` — 按 `agent_metadata.yaml` → `agent.yaml` → `metadata.yaml` 优先级回退加载\n30:    - `save_metadata(workspace_path, metadata)` — 写入 `agent_metadata.yaml`，使用 `yaml.dump(default_flow_style=False, indent=2, sort_keys=False)`\n31:    - `update_metadata(workspace_path, updates)` — 加载 → 合并 → 验证 → 保存 → 返回\n32:    - `validate_workspace(workspace_path)` — 路径存在性 + 语言特定校验\n33:    - `_validate_python_workspace()` — 要求至少一个 `*.py` 文件\n34:    - `_validate_java_workspace()` — 要求 `pom.xml` 存在\n35: \n36: 4. **服务集成**\n37:    - 更新 `agentcube/services/__init__.py` 导出 `MetadataService` 和 `AgentMetadata`\n38:    - `PackRuntime` 通过 `MetadataService` 加载/创建/保存元数据\n39:    - `BuildRuntime` / `PublishRuntime` / `InvokeRuntime` / `StatusRuntime` 正确调用 `MetadataService`\n40: \n41: 5. **错误处理**\n42:    - 工作空间不存在 → `ValueError`\n43:    - Python 工作空间无 `.py` 文件 → `ValueError(\"No Python files found in workspace\")`\n44:    - Java 工作空间无 `pom.xml` → `ValueError`\n45:    - YAML 解析失败 → 包装为有意义的错误\n46:    - Pydantic 验证失败 → 传播 ValidationError\n47: \n48: ### 不包含\n49: \n50: - 元数据版本迁移工具（后续 AR）\n51: - 多工作空间元数据聚合\n52: - 远程元数据同步\n53: - 元数据加密存储\n54: - Go CLI 或其他语言 SDK 的元数据服务\n55: \n56: ## 架构概要\n57: \n58: ### 数据流\n59: \n60: ```\n61: CLI Command (pack/build/publish/invoke/status)\n62:     │\n63:     ▼\n64: Runtime Class (PackRuntime/BuildRuntime/...)\n65:     │\n66:     ├── MetadataService.load_metadata() ──→ agent_metadata.yaml (YAML)\n67:     │         │                                    │\n68:     │         ▼                                    │\n69:     │    AgentMetadata (Pydantic) ◄────────────────┘\n70:     │         │\n71:     │         ├── CLI options merge (MetadataOptions)\n72:     │         │\n73:     │         ├── validate_workspace()\n74:     │         │\n75:     │         └── MetadataService.save_metadata() ──→ agent_metadata.yaml\n76:     │\n77:     └── 业务逻辑（生成 Dockerfile、构建镜像、部署等）\n78: ```\n79: \n80: ### 核心类关系\n81: \n82: | 类 | 职责 | 依赖 |\n83: |----|------|------|\n84: | `AgentMetadata` | 元数据强类型模型，Pydantic 验证 | Pydantic |\n85: | `MetadataOptions` | CLI 选项到元数据的转换中间层 | dataclasses |\n86: | `MetadataService` | 元数据 CRUD + workspace 验证 | AgentMetadata, yaml, pathlib |\n87: | `PackRuntime` | 打包流程编排 | MetadataService, DockerService |\n88: | `BuildRuntime` | 构建流程编排 | MetadataService, DockerService |\n89: | `PublishRuntime` | 发布流程编排 | MetadataService, KubernetesProvider, AgentCubeProvider |\n90: | `InvokeRuntime` | 调用流程编排 | MetadataService |\n91: | `StatusRuntime` | 状态查询编排 | MetadataService |\n92: \n93: ### AgentMetadata 字段定义\n94: \n95: | 字段 | 类型 | 默认值 | 说明 |\n96: |------|------|--------|------|\n97: | `agent_name` | `str` | 必填 | Agent 唯一标识 |\n98: | `description` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | 人类可读描述 |\n99: | `language` | `str` | `\"python\"` | 编程语言（python/java） |\n100: | `entrypoint` | `str` | 必填 | 启动命令 |\n101: | `port` | `int` | `8080` | 暴露端口（1-65535） |\n102: | `build_mode` | `str` | `\"local\"` | 构建策略（local/cloud） |\n103: | `region` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | 部署区域 |\n104: | `version` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | 语义化版本 |\n105: | `image` | `Optional[Dict[str, Any]]` | `None` | 容器镜像信息 |\n106: | `auth` | `Optional[Dict[str, Any]]` | `None` | 认证配置 |\n107: | `requirements_file` | `Optional[str]` | `\"requirements.txt\"` | Python 依赖文件 |\n108: | `registry_url` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | 镜像仓库 URL |\n109: | `registry_username` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | 仓库用户名 |\n110: | `registry_password` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | 仓库密码 |\n111: | `agent_endpoint` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Agent 端点 URL |\n112: | `workload_manager_url` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Workload Manager URL |\n113: | `router_url` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Router URL |\n114: | `readiness_probe_path` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | 就绪探针路径 |\n115: | `readiness_probe_port` | `Optional[int]` | `None` | 就绪探针端口 |\n116: | `agent_id` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | AgentCube 分配的 ID |\n117: | `session_id` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | 会话 ID |\n118: | `k8s_deployment` | `Optional[Dict[str, Any]]` | `None` | K8s 部署信息 |\n119: \n120: ### MetadataOptions 字段定义\n121: \n122: | 字段 | 类型 | 默认值 |\n123: |------|------|--------|\n124: | `agent_name` | `Optional[str]` | `None` |\n125: | `language` | `Optional[str]` | `'python'` |\n126: | `entrypoint` | `Optional[str]` | `None` |\n127: | `port` | `Optional[int]` | `8080` |\n128: | `build_mode` | `Optional[str]` | `'local'` |\n129: | `requirements_file` | `Optional[str]` | `None` |\n130: | `description` | `Optional[str]` | `None` |\n131: | `workload_manager_url` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n132: | `router_url` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n133: | `readiness_probe_path` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n134: | `readiness_probe_port` | `Optional[int]` | `8080` |\n135: | `registry_url` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n136: | `registry_username` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n137: | `registry_password` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n138: | `agent_endpoint` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n139: \n140: ### YAML 持久化格式示例\n141: \n142: ```yaml\n143: agent_name: hello-agent\n144: description: A simple hello world agent\n145: language: python\n146: entrypoint: python main.py\n147: port: 8080\n148: build_mode: local\n149: version: \"0.1.0\"\n150: image:\n151:   name: hello-agent\n152:   tag: \"0.1.0\"\n153: ```\n154: \n155: ## 上游依赖\n156: \n157: | 依赖 | 用途 | 影响 |\n158: |------|------|------|\n159: | `pydantic>=2.0.0` | AgentMetadata 模型定义与验证 | 已有依赖，无新增 |\n160: | `pyyaml>=6.0` | YAML 序列化/反序列化 | 已有依赖，无新增 |\n161: | `packaging>=23.0` | 版本号递增（build 命令使用） | 已有依赖，无新增 |\n162: \n163: ### 受影响的组件\n164: \n165: - **`agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`**（修改/新增）：`MetadataService` 类 + `AgentMetadata` 模型\n166: - **`agentcube/models/pack_models.py`**（新增）：`MetadataOptions` dataclass\n167: - **`agentcube/services/__init__.py`**（修改）：导出 `MetadataService`、`AgentMetadata`\n168: - **`agentcube/runtime/__init__.py`**（修改）：导出 `MetadataOptions`\n169: - **`agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py`**（修改）：通过 `MetadataService` 操作元数据\n170: - **`agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py`**（修改）：通过 `MetadataService` 加载/更新元数据\n171: - **`agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`**（修改）：通过 `MetadataService` 加载/更新元数据\n172: - **`agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py`**（修改）：通过 `MetadataService` 加载元数据\n173: - **`agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py`**（修改）：通过 `MetadataService` 加载元数据\n174: \n175: ### 风险评估\n176: \n177: | 风险 | 等级 | 缓解措施 |\n178: |------|------|----------|\n179: | 旧版 `agentcube.yaml` 文件不兼容 | 中 | 多文件名回退加载 + 迁移提示 |\n180: | Pydantic v2 API 变更 | 低 | 锁定 `pydantic>=2.0.0`，使用稳定 API |\n181: | 并发写入冲突 | 低 | 单用户 CLI 工具，风险低；可加文件锁 |\n182: | 元数据字段缺失导致下游错误 | 中 | Pydantic 验证 + 合理默认值 |\n183: \n184: ## 状态\n185: \n186: - [ ] 提案审查\n187: - [ ] 实现\n188: - [ ] 验证\n\n(End of file - total 188 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-025 — MetadataService 与数据模型\n\n**Module:** cmd/cli\n**Language:** Python\n**Size:** M\n\n## 目的\n\n为 AgentCube CLI 实现元数据服务层与核心数据模型，提供 workspace 元数据的加载、保存、验证和更新能力，支撑 `pack`、`build`、`publish`、`invoke`、`status` 全生命周期的元数据管理。\n\n当前 CLI 各 Runtime 类需要读写 workspace 中的 agent 配置信息，但缺乏统一的服务抽象和强类型数据模型。本 AR 在 `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` 中实现 `MetadataService` 类，在 `agentcube/models/pack_models.py` 中定义 `MetadataOptions` dataclass，并使用 Pydantic `BaseModel` 定义 `AgentMetadata` 模型。\n\n## 范围\n\n### 包含\n\n1. **`AgentMetadata` Pydantic 模型**\n   - 定义在 `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`（或独立模块）\n   - 22 个字段覆盖 agent 名称、语言、入口、端口、构建模式、镜像、认证、端点、探针、K8s 部署等\n   - 3 个 validators：`validate_language`（python/java）、`validate_build_mode`（local/cloud）、`validate_port`（1-65535）","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-025/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775859504826,"end":1775859504833}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775859506131,"sessionID":"ses_28686b59affeAylUCxRXkYiV1W","part":{"id":"prt_d7979974a001c4Cp2WWIFok6Ij","messageID":"msg_d79797d78001NRVIbhv2bR5Vjk","sessionID":"ses_28686b59affeAylUCxRXkYiV1W","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_e0945c0e4a70486982266725","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/cmd/cli/agentcube/services/metadata_service.py"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/cmd/cli/agentcube/services/metadata_service.py</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: \"\"\"Metadata service for loading, saving, and updating agent metadata.\"\"\"\n2: \n3: from __future__ import annotations\n4: \n5: from pathlib import Path\n6: from typing import Any, Dict, List, Optional\n7: \n8: import yaml\n9: from pydantic import BaseModel, Field, field_validator\n10: \n11: \n12: class AgentMetadata(BaseModel):\n13:     \"\"\"Pydantic model representing agent metadata.\"\"\"\n14: \n15:     agent_name: str = Field(..., description=\"Unique name identifying the agent\")\n16:     description: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Human-readable summary\")\n17:     language: str = Field(\"python\", description=\"Programming language used\")\n18:     entrypoint: str = Field(..., description=\"Command to launch the agent\")\n19:     port: int = Field(8080, description=\"Port exposed by the agent runtime\")\n20:     build_mode: str = Field(\"local\", description=\"Build strategy: local or cloud\")\n21:     region: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Deployment region\")\n22:     version: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Semantic version string for publishing\")\n23:     image: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = Field(None, description=\"Container image information\")\n24:     auth: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = Field(None, description=\"Authentication configuration\")\n25:     requirements_file: Optional[str] = Field(\"requirements.txt\", description=\"Python dependency file\")\n26:     registry_url: Optional[str] = Field(\"\", description=\"Registry URL for image publishing\")\n27:     registry_username: Optional[str] = Field(\"\", description=\"Registry username\")\n28:     registry_password: Optional[str] = Field(\"\", description=\"Registry password\")\n29:     agent_endpoint: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Agent endpoint URL\")\n30:     workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"URL for the Workload Manager\")\n31:     router_url: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"URL for the Router\")\n32:     readiness_probe_path: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Path for the readiness probe\")\n33:     readiness_probe_port: Optional[int] = Field(None, description=\"Port for the readiness probe\")\n34:     agent_id: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Agent ID assigned by AgentCube\")\n35:     session_id: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"The session ID for the agent\")\n36:     k8s_deployment: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = Field(None, description=\"Kubernetes deployment information\")\n37: \n38:     @field_validator(\"language\", mode=\"before\")\n39:     @classmethod\n40:     def validate_language(cls, v: Optional[str]) -> str:\n41:         if v is None:\n42:             return \"python\"\n43:         lowered = v.lower()\n44:         if lowered not in (\"python\", \"java\"):\n45:             raise ValueError(f\"Unsupported language: {v}. Must be 'python' or 'java'.\")\n46:         return lowered\n47: \n48:     @field_validator(\"build_mode\", mode=\"before\")\n49:     @classmethod\n50:     def validate_build_mode(cls, v: Optional[str]) -> str:\n51:         if v is None:\n52:             return \"local\"\n53:         lowered = v.lower()\n54:         if lowered not in (\"local\", \"cloud\"):\n55:             raise ValueError(f\"Unsupported build_mode: {v}. Must be 'local' or 'cloud'.\")\n56:         return lowered\n57: \n58:     @field_validator(\"port\")\n59:     @classmethod\n60:     def validate_port(cls, v: int) -> int:\n61:         if v < 1 or v > 65535:\n62:             raise ValueError(f\"Port must be between 1 and 65535, got {v}\")\n63:         return v\n64: \n65: \n66: class MetadataService:\n67:     \"\"\"Service for loading, saving, and updating agent metadata files.\"\"\"\n68: \n69:     METADATA_FILES: List[str] = [\"agent_metadata.yaml\", \"agent.yaml\", \"metadata.yaml\"]\n70: \n71:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None:\n72:         self.verbose = verbose\n73: \n74:     def load_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path) -> Optional[AgentMetadata]:\n75:         \"\"\"Load agent metadata from the workspace directory.\n76: \n77:         Tries files in order: agent_metadata.yaml -> agent.yaml -> metadata.yaml.\n78:         Returns None if no metadata file exists.\n79:         \"\"\"\n80:         for filename in self.METADATA_FILES:\n81:             filepath = workspace_path / filename\n82:             if filepath.exists():\n83:                 with open(filepath, \"r\") as f:\n84:                     data = yaml.safe_load(f)\n85:                 if data is None:\n86:                     data = {}\n87:                 return AgentMetadata(**data)\n88:         return None\n89: \n90:     def save_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None:\n91:         \"\"\"Save agent metadata to agent_metadata.yaml in the workspace directory.\"\"\"\n92:         filepath = workspace_path / \"agent_metadata.yaml\"\n93:         data = metadata.model_dump(exclude_none=True)\n94:         with open(filepath, \"w\") as f:\n95:             yaml.dump(data, f, default_flow_style=False, indent=2, sort_keys=False)\n96: \n97:     def update_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, updates: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata:\n98:         \"\"\"Load existing metadata (or create default), apply updates, save, and return.\"\"\"\n99:         existing = self.load_metadata(workspace_path)\n100:         if existing is None:\n101:             existing = AgentMetadata(\n102:                 agent_name=updates.get(\"agent_name\", workspace_path.name),\n103:                 entrypoint=updates.get(\"entrypoint\", \"\"),\n104:                 language=updates.get(\"language\", \"python\"),\n105:                 port=updates.get(\"port\", 8080),\n106:                 build_mode=updates.get(\"build_mode\", \"local\"),\n107:             )\n108:         merged = existing.model_copy(update=updates)\n109:         self.save_metadata(workspace_path, merged)\n110:         return merged\n111: \n112:     def validate_workspace(self, workspace_path: Path) -> bool:\n113:         \"\"\"Check if the workspace has valid metadata.\"\"\"\n114:         return self.load_metadata(workspace_path) is not None\n115: \n116:     def _validate_python_workspace(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None:\n117:         \"\"\"Validate a Python workspace has required files.\"\"\"\n118:         py_files = list(workspace_path.glob(\"*.py\"))\n119:         if not py_files:\n120:             raise ValueError(\"No Python files found in workspace\")\n121:         req_file = metadata.requirements_file or \"requirements.txt\"\n122:         req_path = workspace_path / req_file\n123:         if not req_path.exists():\n124:             raise ValueError(f\"Dependency file not found: {req_file}\")\n125: \n126:     def _validate_java_workspace(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None:\n127:         \"\"\"Validate a Java workspace has required files.\"\"\"\n128:         pom = workspace_path / \"pom.xml\"\n129:         if not pom.exists():\n130:             raise ValueError(\"pom.xml is required for Java projects\")\n\n(End of file - total 130 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"\"\"\"Metadata service for loading, saving, and updating agent metadata.\"\"\"\n\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import Any, Dict, List, Optional\n\nimport yaml\nfrom pydantic import BaseModel, Field, field_validator\n\n\nclass AgentMetadata(BaseModel):\n    \"\"\"Pydantic model representing agent metadata.\"\"\"\n\n    agent_name: str = Field(..., description=\"Unique name identifying the agent\")\n    description: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Human-readable summary\")\n    language: str = Field(\"python\", description=\"Programming language used\")\n    entrypoint: str = Field(..., description=\"Command to launch the agent\")\n    port: int = Field(8080, description=\"Port exposed by the agent runtime\")\n    build_mode: str = Field(\"local\", description=\"Build strategy: local or cloud\")","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/cmd/cli/agentcube/services/metadata_service.py","time":{"start":1775859506123,"end":1775859506129}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775859507496,"sessionID":"ses_28686b59affeAylUCxRXkYiV1W","part":{"id":"prt_d79799ca4001m16qdSU5LhLTo2","messageID":"msg_d79797d78001NRVIbhv2bR5Vjk","sessionID":"ses_28686b59affeAylUCxRXkYiV1W","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_ea8eb23172c44154986719e7","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/cmd/cli/agentcube/models/pack_models.py"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/cmd/cli/agentcube/models/pack_models.py</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: \"\"\"Data models for the pack command.\"\"\"\n2: \n3: from __future__ import annotations\n4: \n5: from dataclasses import dataclass\n6: from typing import Any, Dict, Optional\n7: \n8: \n9: @dataclass\n10: class MetadataOptions:\n11:     \"\"\"CLI options that map to AgentMetadata fields.\"\"\"\n12: \n13:     agent_name: Optional[str] = None\n14:     language: Optional[str] = \"python\"\n15:     entrypoint: Optional[str] = None\n16:     port: Optional[int] = 8080\n17:     build_mode: Optional[str] = \"local\"\n18:     requirements_file: Optional[str] = None\n19:     description: Optional[str] = None\n20:     workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = \"\"\n21:     router_url: Optional[str] = \"\"\n22:     readiness_probe_path: Optional[str] = \"\"\n23:     readiness_probe_port: Optional[int] = 8080\n24:     registry_url: Optional[str] = \"\"\n25:     registry_username: Optional[str] = \"\"\n26:     registry_password: Optional[str] = \"\"\n27:     agent_endpoint: Optional[str] = \"\"\n28: \n29:     @classmethod\n30:     def from_options(cls, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> \"MetadataOptions\":\n31:         \"\"\"Create a MetadataOptions instance from a dict of CLI options.\n32: \n33:         Unknown fields are silently ignored.\n34:         \"\"\"\n35:         known_fields = {\n36:             \"agent_name\",\n37:             \"language\",\n38:             \"entrypoint\",\n39:             \"port\",\n40:             \"build_mode\",\n41:             \"requirements_file\",\n42:             \"description\",\n43:             \"workload_manager_url\",\n44:             \"router_url\",\n45:             \"readiness_probe_path\",\n46:             \"readiness_probe_port\",\n47:             \"registry_url\",\n48:             \"registry_username\",\n49:             \"registry_password\",\n50:             \"agent_endpoint\",\n51:         }\n52:         filtered = {k: v for k, v in options.items() if k in known_fields}\n53:         return cls(**filtered)\n\n(End of file - total 53 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"\"\"\"Data models for the pack command.\"\"\"\n\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nfrom dataclasses import dataclass\nfrom typing import Any, Dict, Optional\n\n\n@dataclass\nclass MetadataOptions:\n    \"\"\"CLI options that map to AgentMetadata fields.\"\"\"\n\n    agent_name: Optional[str] = None\n    language: Optional[str] = \"python\"\n    entrypoint: Optional[str] = None\n    port: Optional[int] = 8080\n    build_mode: Optional[str] = \"local\"\n    requirements_file: Optional[str] = None\n    description: Optional[str] = None\n    workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = \"\"","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/cmd/cli/agentcube/models/pack_models.py","time":{"start":1775859507488,"end":1775859507494}}}}
