{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775859512218,"sessionID":"ses_28686b59affeAylUCxRXkYiV1W","part":{"id":"prt_d7979af26001CrSIenmNE1mMLg","messageID":"msg_d7979a1a9001tRFZYK3b1b9bLm","sessionID":"ses_28686b59affeAylUCxRXkYiV1W","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_647183b02b22430d88ba75ac","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-023/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-023/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-023 — CLI invoke/status 命令 — Design\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: The `invoke` command sends HTTP POST requests to a deployed agent endpoint and displays the response. The `status` command queries the deployment status of an agent from Kubernetes or workspace metadata and renders it as a Rich Table. Together they complete the agent lifecycle pipeline: `pack → build → publish → invoke/status`.\n6: \n7: Both commands are **not yet implemented** — this design specifies the full technical implementation.\n8: \n9: ---\n10: \n11: ## Architecture\n12: \n13: ### 2.1 Data Flow\n14: \n15: ```\n16: ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n17: │                          CLI (Typer)                                  │\n18: │   kubectl-agentcube invoke -f <ws> --payload '{}' [--header ...]     │\n19: │   kubectl-agentcube status -f <ws> [--provider agentcube|k8s]        │\n20: └────────────────────────┬─────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n21:                          │\n22:           ┌──────────────┴──────────────┐\n23:           ▼                             ▼\n24: ┌─────────────────────┐       ┌─────────────────────┐\n25: │    InvokeRuntime    │       │    StatusRuntime    │\n26: │                     │       │                     │\n27: │ .invoke()           │       │ .get_status()       │\n28: │  ├─ _validate_      │       │  ├─ load metadata   │\n29: │  │   prerequisites  │       │  ├─ _get_cr_k8s_    │\n30: │  ├─ _invoke_agent_  │       │  │   status()        │\n31: │  │   via_agentcube  │       │  └─ _get_k8s_       │\n32: │  └─ _direct_http_   │       │     status()        │\n33: │     invocation()    │       │                     │\n34: └────────┬────────────┘       └────────┬────────────┘\n35:          │                             │\n36:          ▼                             ▼\n37: ┌─────────────────────┐       ┌─────────────────────┐\n38: │  httpx / requests   │       │ AgentCubeProvider   │\n39: │  POST → endpoint    │       │ KubernetesProvider  │\n40: └─────────────────────┘       └────────┬────────────┘\n41:                                        │\n42:                                        ▼\n43:                               ┌─────────────────────┐\n44:                               │   Rich Table Output │\n45:                               │   Field | Value     │\n46:                               └─────────────────────┘\n47: ```\n48: \n49: ### 2.2 Package Layout (invoke/status-relevant modules)\n50: \n51: ```\n52: cmd/cli/\n53: ├── pyproject.toml                     — Dependencies, console script entry\n54: ├── agentcube/\n55: │   ├── __init__.py                    — __version__, exports (add InvokeRuntime, StatusRuntime)\n56: │   ├── cli/\n57: │   │   ├── __init__.py                — Subpackage marker\n58: │   │   └── main.py                    — Typer app, invoke(), status(), _handle_error\n59: │   ├── models/\n60: │   │   └── pack_models.py             — MetadataOptions dataclass\n61: │   ├── runtime/\n62: │   │   ├── __init__.py                — Re-exports (add InvokeRuntime, StatusRuntime)\n63: │   │   ├── invoke_runtime.py          — InvokeRuntime class (NEW)\n64: │   │   └── status_runtime.py          — StatusRuntime class (NEW)\n65: │   └── services/\n66: │       ├── __init__.py                — Services package docstring\n67: │       ├── metadata_service.py         — AgentMetadata, MetadataService\n68: │       ├── docker_service.py           — DockerService\n69: │       ├── k8s_provider.py             — KubernetesProvider (add get_agent_status)\n70: │       └── agentcube_provider.py       — AgentCubeProvider (get_agent_runtime exists)\n71: └── tests/\n72:     ├── cli/\n73:     │   ├── test_invoke_command.py     — CLI invoke command tests (NEW)\n74:     │   └── test_status_command.py     — CLI status command tests (NEW)\n75:     └── runtime/\n76:         ├── test_invoke_runtime.py     — InvokeRuntime unit tests (NEW)\n77:         └── test_status_runtime.py     — StatusRuntime unit tests (NEW)\n78: ```\n79: \n80: ### 2.3 Dependencies\n81: \n82: | Module | Purpose |\n83: |--------|---------|\n84: | `typer[all]>=0.9.0` | CLI framework, Rich markup |\n85: | `pydantic>=2.0.0` | AgentMetadata validation |\n86: | `pyyaml>=6.0` | YAML load/dump for agent_metadata.yaml |\n87: | `httpx>=0.24.0` | HTTP client for invoke requests |\n88: | `rich>=13.0.0` | Progress spinner, colored output, tables |\n89: | `kubernetes>=28.0.0` | K8s client library (optional, for status providers) |\n90: \n91: No new dependencies are introduced — all are already declared in `pyproject.toml`.\n92: \n93: ---\n94: \n95: ## Component Design\n96: \n97: ### 3.1 InvokeRuntime (`agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py`)\n98: \n99: ```python\n100: class InvokeRuntime:\n101:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\") -> None: ...\n102:     def invoke(\n103:         self,\n104:         workspace_path: Path,\n105:         payload: Dict[str, Any],\n106:         headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n107:     ) -> Any: ...\n108:     def _validate_invoke_prerequisites(\n109:         self, workspace_path: Path\n110:     ) -> Tuple[AgentMetadata, str, str]: ...\n111:     async def _invoke_agent_via_agentcube(\n112:         self,\n113:         agent_id: str,\n114:         payload: Dict[str, Any],\n115:         headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]],\n116:         endpoint: str,\n117:         workspace_path: Path,\n118:     ) -> Any: ...\n119:     async def _direct_http_invocation(\n120:         self,\n121:         endpoint: str,\n122:         payload: Dict[str, Any],\n123:         headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]],\n124:         workspace_path: Path,\n125:     ) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n126: ```\n127: \n128: #### 3.1.1 `invoke()` — Main orchestration\n129: \n130: ```python\n131: def invoke(self, workspace_path: Path, payload: Dict[str, Any], headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None) -> Any:\n132:     # 1. Validate prerequisites — returns (metadata, agent_id, endpoint)\n133:     metadata, agent_id, endpoint = self._validate_invoke_prerequisites(workspace_path)\n134: \n135:     # 2. Route by provider\n136:     if self.provider == \"agentcube\":\n137:         return asyncio.run(\n138:             self._invoke_agent_via_agentcube(agent_id, payload, headers, endpoint, workspace_path)\n139:         )\n140:     else:\n141:         return asyncio.run(\n142:             self._direct_http_invocation(endpoint, payload, headers, workspace_path)\n143:         )\n144: ```\n145: \n146: #### 3.1.2 `_validate_invoke_prerequisites()`\n147: \n148: Loads metadata and validates that the agent has been published:\n149: \n150: ```python\n151: def _validate_invoke_prerequisites(self, workspace_path: Path) -> Tuple[AgentMetadata, str, str]:\n152:     service = MetadataService(verbose=self.verbose)\n153:     metadata = service.load_metadata(workspace_path)\n154: \n155:     if not metadata.agent_id:\n156:         raise ValueError(\"Agent has not been published. Run 'kubectl-agentcube publish' first.\")\n157:     if not metadata.agent_endpoint:\n158:         raise ValueError(\"Agent endpoint is not set in metadata. Run 'kubectl-agentcube publish' first.\")\n159: \n160:     return metadata, metadata.agent_id, metadata.agent_endpoint\n161: ```\n162: \n163: #### 3.1.3 `_invoke_agent_via_agentcube()` — AgentRuntime CR invocation\n164: \n165: Key behaviors:\n166: - **URL rewriting**: If `metadata.k8s_deployment.type == \"AgentRuntime\"`, rewrite endpoint to:\n167:   ```\n168:   {base}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/\n169:   ```\n170:   where `base` is extracted from the original endpoint, `namespace` and `agent_name` come from `metadata.k8s_deployment`.\n171: - **Session header**: If `metadata.session_id` exists, add `X-Agentcube-Session-Id` header.\n172: - **HTTP POST**: Uses `httpx.AsyncClient` to POST JSON payload.\n173: \n174: **Known issue**: The existing implementation only assigns `response` inside `if endpoint.startswith(\"http\"):` — if the condition is false, `return response` raises `UnboundLocalError`. This is out of scope for AR-023 but the CLI layer will catch it via `_handle_error`.\n175: \n176: ```python\n177: async def _invoke_agent_via_agentcube(self, agent_id, payload, headers, endpoint, workspace_path):\n178:     metadata = MetadataService(verbose=self.verbose).load_metadata(workspace_path)\n179: \n180:     # URL rewriting for AgentRuntime CR\n181:     if metadata.k8s_deployment and metadata.k8s_deployment.get(\"type\") == \"AgentRuntime\":\n182:         namespace = metadata.k8s_deployment.get(\"namespace\", \"default\")\n183:         agent_name = metadata.k8s_deployment.get(\"cr_name\", metadata.agent_name)\n184:         # Extract base URL from original endpoint\n185:         base = endpoint.rstrip(\"/\").rsplit(\"/v1/\", 1)[0] if \"/v1/\" in endpoint else endpoint.rstrip(\"/\")\n186:         endpoint = f\"{base}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/\"\n187: \n188:     # Build headers\n189:     request_headers = headers.copy() if headers else {}\n190:     if metadata.session_id:\n191:         request_headers[\"X-Agentcube-Session-Id\"] = metadata.session_id\n192: \n193:     # POST via httpx\n194:     async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n195:         response = await client.post(endpoint, json=payload, headers=request_headers)\n196:         response.raise_for_status()\n197:         return response.json()\n198: ```\n199: \n200: #### 3.1.4 `_direct_http_invocation()` — Standard K8s invocation\n201: \n202: Direct HTTP POST to the agent endpoint (NodePort Service URL):\n203: \n204: ```python\n205: async def _direct_http_invocation(self, endpoint, payload, headers, workspace_path):\n206:     metadata = MetadataService(verbose=self.verbose).load_metadata(workspace_path)\n207: \n208:     request_headers = headers.copy() if headers else {}\n209:     if metadata.session_id:\n210:         request_headers[\"X-Agentcube-Session-Id\"] = metadata.session_id\n211: \n212:     async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n213:         response = await client.post(endpoint, json=payload, headers=request_headers)\n214:         response.raise_for_status()\n215:         return response.json()\n216: ```\n217: \n218: ### 3.2 StatusRuntime (`agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py`)\n219: \n220: ```python\n221: class StatusRuntime:\n222:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\") -> None: ...\n223:     def get_status(\n224:         self, workspace_path: Path, provider: Optional[str] = None\n225:     ) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n226:     def _get_k8s_status(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n227:     def _get_cr_k8s_status(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n228: ```\n229: \n230: #### 3.2.1 `get_status()` — Main orchestration\n231: \n232: ```python\n233: def get_status(self, workspace_path: Path, provider: Optional[str] = None) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n234:     provider = provider or self.provider\n235:     service = MetadataService(verbose=self.verbose)\n236:     metadata = service.load_metadata(workspace_path)\n237: \n238:     if not metadata.agent_id:\n239:         return {\"status\": \"not_published\"}\n240: \n241:     if provider == \"agentcube\":\n242:         return self._get_cr_k8s_status(metadata)\n243:     else:\n244:         return self._get_k8s_status(metadata)\n245: ```\n246: \n247: #### 3.2.2 `_get_cr_k8s_status()` — AgentRuntime CR status\n248: \n249: ```python\n250: def _get_cr_k8s_status(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n251:     namespace = metadata.k8s_deployment.get(\"namespace\", \"default\") if metadata.k8s_deployment else \"default\"\n252:     cr_name = metadata.k8s_deployment.get(\"cr_name\", metadata.agent_name) if metadata.k8s_deployment else metadata.agent_name\n253: \n254:     provider = AgentCubeProvider(namespace=namespace, verbose=self.verbose)\n255:     cr_object = provider.get_agent_runtime(cr_name)\n256: \n257:     if cr_object is None:\n258:         return {\n259:             \"status\": \"not_found_in_k8s\",\n260:             \"agent_name\": metadata.agent_name,\n261:             \"cr_name\": cr_name,\n262:             \"namespace\": namespace,\n263:         }\n264: \n265:     cr_status = cr_object.get(\"status\", {})\n266:     if cr_status:\n267:         return {\n268:             \"status\": cr_status.get(\"status\", \"unknown\"),\n269:             \"agent_name\": metadata.agent_name,\n270:             \"endpoint\": cr_status.get(\"agentEndpoint\", metadata.agent_endpoint),\n271:             \"cr_name\": cr_name,\n272:             \"namespace\": namespace,\n273:             \"version\": metadata.version,\n274:         }\n275:     else:\n276:         return {\n277:             \"status\": \"created_no_status\",\n278:             \"agent_name\": metadata.agent_name,\n279:             \"cr_name\": cr_name,\n280:             \"namespace\": namespace,\n281:             \"version\": metadata.version,\n282:         }\n283: ```\n284: \n285: #### 3.2.3 `_get_k8s_status()` — Standard K8s deployment status\n286: \n287: Requires `KubernetesProvider.get_agent_status()` to be added (see §3.4):\n288: \n289: ```python\n290: def _get_k8s_status(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n291:     namespace = metadata.k8s_deployment.get(\"namespace\", \"default\") if metadata.k8s_deployment else \"default\"\n292:     deployment_name = metadata.k8s_deployment.get(\"deployment_name\", metadata.agent_name) if metadata.k8s_deployment else metadata.agent_name\n293: \n294:     provider = KubernetesProvider(namespace=namespace, verbose=self.verbose)\n295:     return provider.get_agent_status(deployment_name)\n296: ```\n297: \n298: ### 3.3 CLI Commands (`agentcube/cli/main.py`)\n299: \n300: #### 3.3.1 `invoke` command\n301: \n302: ```python\n303: @app.command()\n304: def invoke(\n305:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory.\", show_default=True),\n306:     payload: str = typer.Option(\"{}\", \"--payload\", help=\"JSON-formatted input passed to the agent.\"),\n307:     header_list: Optional[List[str]] = typer.Option(None, \"--header\", help=\"Custom HTTP headers (e.g., 'Authorization: Bearer token'). Can be specified multiple times.\"),\n308:     provider: str = typer.Option(\"agentcube\", \"--provider\", help=\"Target provider: 'agentcube' (AgentRuntime CR) or 'k8s' (Deployment/Service).\"),\n309:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging.\"),\n310: ) -> None:\n311:     \"\"\"Invoke a deployed agent with a JSON payload.\"\"\"\n312: ```\n313: \n314: **Implementation flow:**\n315: 1. Parse `payload` as JSON — on failure, print error in red and `typer.Exit(1)` (before `_handle_error`)\n316: 2. Parse `header_list` — split each on first `:` to produce `Dict[str, str]`; on invalid format, print error and `typer.Exit(1)`\n317: 3. Instantiate `InvokeRuntime(verbose=verbose, provider=provider)`\n318: 4. Call `runtime.invoke(Path(workspace), payload_dict, headers)`\n319: 5. Print response (Rich-formatted JSON if dict, raw text otherwise)\n320: 6. On exception, call `_handle_error(e, \"invoking agent\", verbose)`\n321: \n322: #### 3.3.2 `status` command\n323: \n324: ```python\n325: @app.command()\n326: def status(\n327:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory.\", show_default=True),\n328:     provider: str = typer.Option(\"agentcube\", \"--provider\", help=\"Target provider: 'agentcube' (AgentRuntime CR) or 'k8s' (Deployment/Service).\"),\n329:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging.\"),\n330: ) -> None:\n331:     \"\"\"Check the status of a deployed agent.\"\"\"\n332: ```\n333: \n334: **Implementation flow:**\n335: 1. Instantiate `StatusRuntime(verbose=verbose, provider=provider)`\n336: 2. Call `runtime.get_status(Path(workspace), provider)`\n337: 3. If `status == \"not_published\"`: print guidance to run `publish` first, `typer.Exit(1)`\n338: 4. If `status == \"error\"`: print error details, `typer.Exit(1)`\n339: 5. Render Rich `Table` with columns: Field, Value\n340: 6. On exception (not `typer.Exit`), call `_handle_error(e, \"getting status\", verbose)`\n341: \n342: ### 3.4 KubernetesProvider extension\n343: \n344: Add `get_agent_status()` method to `KubernetesProvider`:\n345: \n346: ```python\n347: def get_agent_status(self, agent_name: str) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n348:     \"\"\"Get the status of a deployed agent.\n349: \n350:     Args:\n351:         agent_name: Name of the deployment.\n352: \n353:     Returns:\n354:         Dict with status, replicas, ready_replicas, available_replicas, etc.\n355:     \"\"\"\n356:     try:\n357:         deployment = self._apps_api.read_namespaced_deployment_status(\n358:             name=agent_name,\n359:             namespace=self.namespace,\n360:         )\n361:         status = deployment.status\n362:         return {\n363:             \"status\": \"running\" if (status.ready_replicas and status.ready_replicas > 0) else \"pending\",\n364:             \"deployment_name\": agent_name,\n365:             \"namespace\": self.namespace,\n366:             \"replicas\": status.replicas,\n367:             \"ready_replicas\": status.ready_replicas,\n368:             \"available_replicas\": status.available_replicas,\n369:             \"updated_replicas\": status.updated_replicas,\n370:         }\n371:     except ApiException as e:\n372:         if e.status == 404:\n373:             return {\n374:                 \"status\": \"not_found\",\n375:                 \"deployment_name\": agent_name,\n376:                 \"namespace\": self.namespace,\n377:             }\n378:         raise\n379: ```\n380: \n381: ### 3.5 Sentinel Errors\n382: \n383: ```python\n384: # InvokeRuntime\n385: ValueError(\"Agent has not been published. Run 'kubectl-agentcube publish' first.\")\n386: ValueError(\"Agent endpoint is not set in metadata. Run 'kubectl-agentcube publish' first.\")\n387: \n388: # StatusRuntime\n389: # Returns dict with status field — no exceptions for logical states\n390: \n391: # CLI layer\n392: typer.Exit(1) — invalid JSON payload\n393: typer.Exit(1) — invalid header format\n394: typer.Exit(1) — not_published status\n395: typer.Exit(1) — error status\n396: ```\n397: \n398: ---\n399: \n400: ## Data Flow Details\n401: \n402: ### 4.1 invoke() CLI → Runtime → HTTP\n403: \n404: ```\n405: CLI invoke()\n406:   │\n407:   ├── json.loads(payload) ──→ JSONDecodeError → print error, exit 1\n408:   │\n409:   ├── parse headers ──→ invalid format → print error, exit 1\n410:   │\n411:   ├── InvokeRuntime.invoke(workspace, payload_dict, headers)\n412:   │     │\n413:   │     ├── _validate_invoke_prerequisites()\n414:   │     │     ├── MetadataService.load_metadata()\n415:   │     │     ├── check metadata.agent_id → ValueError if missing\n416:   │     │     └── check metadata.agent_endpoint → ValueError if missing\n417:   │     │\n418:   │     └── provider == \"agentcube\"?\n419:   │           ├── YES → _invoke_agent_via_agentcube()\n420:   │           │         ├── URL rewrite if k8s_deployment.type == \"AgentRuntime\"\n421:   │           │         ├── Add X-Agentcube-Session-Id if session_id exists\n422:   │           │         └── httpx.AsyncClient.post(endpoint, json=payload, headers=headers)\n423:   │           │\n424:   │           └── NO → _direct_http_invocation()\n425:   │                     ├── Add X-Agentcube-Session-Id if session_id exists\n426:   │                     └── httpx.AsyncClient.post(endpoint, json=payload, headers=headers)\n427:   │\n428:   └── Print response (JSON-formatted or raw text)\n429: ```\n430: \n431: ### 4.2 status() CLI → Runtime → K8s API → Rich Table\n432: \n433: ```\n434: CLI status()\n435:   │\n436:   ├── StatusRuntime.get_status(workspace, provider)\n437:   │     │\n438:   │     ├── MetadataService.load_metadata()\n439:   │     ├── check metadata.agent_id → return {\"status\": \"not_published\"} if missing\n440:   │     │\n441:   │     └── provider == \"agentcube\"?\n442:   │           ├── YES → _get_cr_k8s_status()\n443:   │           │         ├── AgentCubeProvider.get_agent_runtime(cr_name)\n444:   │           │         ├── CR not found → {\"status\": \"not_found_in_k8s\", ...}\n445:   │           │         ├── CR has status → {\"status\": cr_status[\"status\"], \"endpoint\": ..., ...}\n446:   │           │         └── CR exists but no status → {\"status\": \"created_no_status\", ...}\n447:   │           │\n448:   │           └── NO → _get_k8s_status()\n449:   │                     ├── KubernetesProvider.get_agent_status(deployment_name)\n450:   │                     ├── Deployment not found → {\"status\": \"not_found\", ...}\n451:   │                     └── Deployment found → {\"status\": \"running\"/\"pending\", replicas, ...}\n452:   │\n453:   ├── status == \"not_published\"? → print guidance, exit 1\n454:   ├── status == \"error\"? → print error, exit 1\n455:   │\n456:   └── Render Rich Table:\n457:         ┌─────────────────┬──────────────────┐\n458:         │ Field           │ Value            │\n459:         ├─────────────────┼──────────────────┤\n460:         │ Agent Name      │ test-agent       │\n461:         │ Status          │ running          │\n462:         │ Endpoint        │ http://...       │\n463:         │ Version         │ v1.0.0           │\n464:         │ Provider        │ agentcube        │\n465:         │ ...             │ ...              │\n466:         └─────────────────┴──────────────────┘\n467: ```\n468: \n469: ### 4.3 Header parsing logic\n470: \n471: ```python\n472: headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None\n473: if header_list:\n474:     headers = {}\n475:     for h in header_list:\n476:         if \":\" not in h:\n477:             typer.echo(f\"Error: Invalid header format '{h}'. Expected 'key:value'.\", err=True)\n478:             raise typer.Exit(1)\n479:         key, value = h.split(\":\", 1)\n480:         headers[key.strip()] = value.strip()\n481: ```\n482: \n483: ### 4.4 URL rewriting for AgentRuntime CR\n484: \n485: When `k8s_deployment.type == \"AgentRuntime\"`:\n486: \n487: ```python\n488: namespace = metadata.k8s_deployment.get(\"namespace\", \"default\")\n489: agent_name = metadata.k8s_deployment.get(\"cr_name\", metadata.agent_name)\n490: base = endpoint.rstrip(\"/\").rsplit(\"/v1/\", 1)[0] if \"/v1/\" in endpoint else endpoint.rstrip(\"/\")\n491: endpoint = f\"{base}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/\"\n492: ```\n493: \n494: ---\n495: \n496: ## Error Handling\n497: \n498: ### 5.1 Error Handling Strategy\n499: \n500: | Error Type | Handling | Exit Code |\n501: |------------|----------|-----------|\n502: | Invalid JSON payload | Print error in red, exit immediately | 1 |\n503: | Invalid header format | Print error in red, exit immediately | 1 |\n504: | Agent not published (invoke) | `_handle_error(e, \"invoking agent\", verbose)` | 1 |\n505: | Agent endpoint missing (invoke) | `_handle_error(e, \"invoking agent\", verbose)` | 1 |\n506: | HTTP error during invoke | `_handle_error(e, \"invoking agent\", verbose)` | 1 |\n507: | K8s client init failure (status) | `_handle_error(e, \"getting status\", verbose)` | 1 |\n508: | not_published status | Print guidance, exit immediately | 1 |\n509: | error status | Print error details, exit immediately | 1 |\n510: | CR not found in K8s (status) | Display in table as status field | 0 |\n511: | Deployment not found (status) | Display in table as status field | 0 |\n512: \n513: ### 5.2 CLI Error Handler (existing, reused)\n514: \n515: ```python\n516: def _handle_error(e: Exception, command_name: str, verbose: bool) -> None:\n517:     console.print(f\"[red]Error {command_name}: {e}[/red]\")\n518:     if verbose:\n519:         console.print_exception()\n520:     raise typer.Exit(1)\n521: ```\n522: \n523: ### 5.3 Verbose vs Global Verbose\n524: \n525: The subcommand's local `--verbose` flag is passed to `_handle_error`, ensuring traceback is printed even if global `-v` was not passed on the root callback.\n526: \n527: ---\n528: \n529: ## Testing Strategy\n530: \n531: ### 6.1 Unit Test Matrix\n532: \n533: #### InvokeRuntime Tests (`tests/runtime/test_invoke_runtime.py`)\n534: \n535: | Test Name | Description |\n536: |-----------|-------------|\n537: | `TestInvokeRuntime_ValidInvokeAgentCube` | Valid workspace, agentcube provider → invokes successfully |\n538: | `TestInvokeRuntime_ValidInvokeK8s` | Valid workspace, k8s provider → direct HTTP invocation |\n539: | `TestInvokeRuntime_NotPublished` | No agent_id in metadata → `ValueError` |\n540: | `TestInvokeRuntime_MissingEndpoint` | No agent_endpoint in metadata → `ValueError` |\n541: | `TestInvokeRuntime_URLRewriting` | k8s_deployment.type == \"AgentRuntime\" → endpoint rewritten |\n542: | `TestInvokeRuntime_SessionHeader` | session_id in metadata → X-Agentcube-Session-Id header added |\n543: | `TestInvokeRuntime_CustomHeaders` | Custom headers passed through |\n544: | `TestInvokeRuntime_HTTPError` | Non-2xx response → exception raised |\n545: | `TestInvokeRuntime_UnboundLocalError` | Known bug: non-http endpoint → caught by CLI _handle_error |\n546: \n547: #### StatusRuntime Tests (`tests/runtime/test_status_runtime.py`)\n548: \n549: | Test Name | Description |\n550: |-----------|-------------|\n551: | `TestStatusRuntime_NotPublished` | No agent_id → `{\"status\": \"not_published\"}` |\n552: | `TestStatusRuntime_CRAgentCubeExists` | CR exists with status → correct status dict |\n553: | `TestStatusRuntime_CRAgentCubeNoStatus` | CR exists but no status field → `{\"status\": \"created_no_status\"}` |\n554: | `TestStatusRuntime_CRNotFound` | CR not found → `{\"status\": \"not_found_in_k8s\"}` |\n555: | `TestStatusRuntime_K8sDeploymentRunning` | K8s deployment ready → `{\"status\": \"running\", ...}` |\n556: | `TestStatusRuntime_K8sDeploymentPending` | K8s deployment not ready → `{\"status\": \"pending\", ...}` |\n557: | `TestStatusRuntime_K8sDeploymentNotFound` | K8s deployment 404 → `{\"status\": \"not_found\", ...}` |\n558: | `TestStatusRuntime_ProviderSelection` | Provider parameter routes to correct method |\n559: \n560: #### CLI invoke Command Tests (`tests/cli/test_invoke_command.py`)\n561: \n562: | Test Name | Description |\n563: |-----------|-------------|\n564: | `TestInvokeCommand_SuccessAgentCube` | `invoke --provider agentcube` → success output, exit 0 |\n565: | `TestInvokeCommand_SuccessK8s` | `invoke --provider k8s` → success output, exit 0 |\n566: | `TestInvokeCommand_DefaultPayload` | `invoke` (no --payload) → uses `\"{}\"` |\n567: | `TestInvokeCommand_CustomPayload` | `invoke --payload '{\"key\":\"value\"}'` → correct JSON parsed |\n568: | `TestInvokeCommand_InvalidPayload` | `invoke --payload '{bad}'` → error, exit 1 |\n569: | `TestInvokeCommand_SingleHeader` | `invoke --header \"Authorization: Bearer token\"` → parsed |\n570: | `TestInvokeCommand_MultipleHeaders` | `invoke --header \"A:1\" --header \"B:2\"` → merged |\n571: | `TestInvokeCommand_InvalidHeader` | `invoke --header \"BadHeader\"` → error, exit 1 |\n572: | `TestInvokeCommand_VerboseError` | Exception + `--verbose` → red error + traceback, exit 1 |\n573: | `TestInvokeCommand_QuietError` | Exception, no `--verbose` → red error only, exit 1 |\n574: | `TestInvokeCommand_HelpOutput` | `invoke --help` → shows all options |\n575: \n576: #### CLI status Command Tests (`tests/cli/test_status_command.py`)\n577: \n578: | Test Name | Description |\n579: |-----------|-------------|\n580: | `TestStatusCommand_SuccessAgentCube` | `status --provider agentcube` → Rich Table, exit 0 |\n581: | `TestStatusCommand_SuccessK8s` | `status --provider k8s` → Rich Table, exit 0 |\n582: | `TestStatusCommand_NotPublished` | No agent_id → guidance message, exit 1 |\n583: | `TestStatusCommand_ErrorStatus` | status == \"error\" → error message, exit 1 |\n584: | `TestStatusCommand_VerboseError` | Exception + `--verbose` → red error + traceback, exit 1 |\n585: | `TestStatusCommand_QuietError` | Exception, no `--verbose` → red error only, exit 1 |\n586: | `TestStatusCommand_HelpOutput` | `status --help` → shows all options |\n587: \n588: #### KubernetesProvider Tests (extension) (`tests/services/test_k8s_provider.py`)\n589: \n590: | Test Name | Description |\n591: |-----------|-------------|\n592: | `TestK8sProvider_GetAgentStatusRunning` | Deployment ready → `{\"status\": \"running\", ...}` |\n593: | `TestK8sProvider_GetAgentStatusPending` | Deployment not ready → `{\"status\": \"pending\", ...}` |\n594: | `TestK8sProvider_GetAgentStatusNotFound` | 404 → `{\"status\": \"not_found\", ...}` |\n595: \n596: ### 6.2 Test Helpers\n597: \n598: ```python\n599: @pytest.fixture\n600: def workspace_with_published_metadata(tmp_path: Path) -> Path:\n601:     ws = tmp_path / \"my-agent\"\n602:     ws.mkdir()\n603:     (ws / \"main.py\").write_text(\"print('hello')\\n\")\n604:     (ws / \"agent_metadata.yaml\").write_text(\n605:         \"agent_name: test-agent\\n\"\n606:         \"language: python\\n\"\n607:         \"entrypoint: python main.py\\n\"\n608:         \"port: 8080\\n\"\n609:         \"build_mode: local\\n\"\n610:         \"agent_id: test-agent-123\\n\"\n611:         \"agent_endpoint: http://router.example.com/v1/agents/test-agent\\n\"\n612:         \"k8s_deployment:\\n\"\n613:         \"  type: AgentRuntime\\n\"\n614:         \"  namespace: default\\n\"\n615:         \"  cr_name: test-agent\\n\"\n616:     )\n617:     return ws\n618: \n619: @pytest.fixture\n620: def mock_httpx_client(mocker):\n621:     mock_response = MagicMock()\n622:     mock_response.json.return_value = {\"output\": \"hello world\"}\n623:     mock_response.raise_for_status.return_value = None\n624: \n625:     mock_client = MagicMock()\n626:     mock_client.__aenter__ = AsyncMock(return_value=mock_client)\n627:     mock_client.__aexit__ = AsyncMock(return_value=None)\n628:     mock_client.post.return_value = mock_response\n629: \n630:     mocker.patch(\"httpx.AsyncClient\", return_value=mock_client)\n631:     return mock_client\n632: ```\n633: \n634: ### 6.3 Mock Strategy\n635: \n636: - **Filesystem:** Use `pytest` `tmp_path` fixture for isolated workspaces\n637: - **MetadataService:** Real instance (lightweight, no external deps)\n638: - **httpx.AsyncClient:** Mock `post()`, `__aenter__`, `__aexit__`\n639: - **AgentCubeProvider:** Mock `get_agent_runtime()`\n640: - **KubernetesProvider:** Mock `get_agent_status()`\n641: - **Console output:** Capture via `capfd` or `rich.console.Console(record=True)`\n642: \n643: ### 6.4 Gate Requirements\n644: \n645: 1. `pytest tests/ -v` all pass\n646: 2. `pytest tests/ --cov=agentcube --cov-report=term-missing` coverage ≥ 80%\n647: 3. `ruff check agentcube/` no violations\n648: 4. `mypy agentcube/` no type errors\n649: 5. All InvokeRuntime and StatusRuntime public methods have unit tests\n650: 6. Error paths tested (invalid payload, invalid header, not published, HTTP errors)\n651: 7. Both provider flows tested (agentcube and k8s) for invoke and status\n652: \n653: ---\n654: \n655: ## Implementation Notes\n656: \n657: 1. **async/await in CLI**: `InvokeRuntime` uses `async` methods internally but the CLI command runs them synchronously via `asyncio.run()`. This avoids making the Typer command async.\n658: \n659: 2. **httpx vs requests**: The invoke command uses `httpx` (already a dependency) for async HTTP. The Python SDK uses `requests`, but the CLI layer should use `httpx` for consistency with the async pattern in `InvokeRuntime`.\n660: \n661: 3. **URL rewriting edge case**: If the original endpoint doesn't contain `/v1/`, the base URL extraction falls back to the full endpoint (stripped of trailing slashes). This handles both `http://router/v1/...` and `http://localhost:30080` formats.\n662: \n663: 4. **Session header spelling**: The header is `X-Agentcube-Session-Id` (note: not `X-AgentCube-Session-Id`). This matches the SDK's `SESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"` (lowercase, HTTP headers are case-insensitive).\n664: \n665: 5. **Provider default**: Both commands default to `provider=\"agentcube\"`, consistent with the `publish` command.\n666: \n667: 6. **KubernetesProvider.get_agent_status()**: This method does not exist yet and must be added. It queries `read_namespaced_deployment_status()` and returns a dict with status fields. 404 is handled gracefully (returns `not_found` status dict, not an exception).\n668: \n669: 7. **Known UnboundLocalError**: `InvokeRuntime._invoke_agent_via_agentcube` has a known bug where `response` is only assigned inside `if endpoint.startswith(\"http\"):`. If the endpoint doesn't start with `http`, `return response` raises `UnboundLocalError`. This is out of scope for AR-023 — the CLI layer catches it via `_handle_error` and the user sees a friendly error message.\n670: \n671: 8. **Rich Table rendering**: The status command renders a table with all key-value pairs from the status dict. The table should include at minimum: Agent Name, Status, Endpoint, Version, Provider.\n672: \n673: 9. **No new dependencies**: All required libraries (httpx, rich, typer, pydantic, pyyaml, kubernetes) are already declared in `pyproject.toml`.\n674: \n675: 10. **runtime/__init__.py update**: After creating `invoke_runtime.py` and `status_runtime.py`, update `runtime/__init__.py` to export `InvokeRuntime` and `StatusRuntime`.\n676: \n677: 11. **agentcube/__init__.py update**: After creating the runtime classes, update the top-level `__init__.py` to include `InvokeRuntime` and `StatusRuntime` in exports (note: `StatusRuntime` was explicitly not exported before — this AR adds it).\n\n(End of file - total 677 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-023 — CLI invoke/status 命令 — Design\n\n## Overview\n\nThe `invoke` command sends HTTP POST requests to a deployed agent endpoint and displays the response. The `status` command queries the deployment status of an agent from Kubernetes or workspace metadata and renders it as a Rich Table. Together they complete the agent lifecycle pipeline: `pack → build → publish → invoke/status`.\n\nBoth commands are **not yet implemented** — this design specifies the full technical implementation.\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\n### 2.1 Data Flow\n\n```\n┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                          CLI (Typer)                                  │\n│   kubectl-agentcube invoke -f <ws> --payload '{}' [--header ...]     │\n│   kubectl-agentcube status -f <ws> [--provider agentcube|k8s]        │\n└────────────────────────┬─────────────────────────────────────────────┘","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-023/design.md","time":{"start":1775859512207,"end":1775859512215}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775859513645,"sessionID":"ses_28686b59affeAylUCxRXkYiV1W","part":{"id":"prt_d7979b42f001zkz8Hgq0SoZNx2","messageID":"msg_d7979a1a9001tRFZYK3b1b9bLm","sessionID":"ses_28686b59affeAylUCxRXkYiV1W","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_8f31b9daa59849a9a7705266","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: \"\"\"PackRuntime - orchestrates the agent workspace packaging lifecycle.\"\"\"\n2: \n3: from __future__ import annotations\n4: \n5: import xml.etree.ElementTree as ET\n6: from dataclasses import asdict\n7: from pathlib import Path\n8: from typing import Any, Dict, Optional\n9: \n10: from agentcube.models.pack_models import MetadataOptions\n11: from agentcube.services.metadata_service import AgentMetadata, MetadataService\n12: \n13: \n14: class PackRuntime:\n15:     \"\"\"Orchestrates validation, metadata merging, and Dockerfile generation for an agent workspace.\"\"\"\n16: \n17:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None:\n18:         self.verbose = verbose\n19:         self.metadata_service = MetadataService(verbose=verbose)\n20: \n21:     def pack(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n22:         \"\"\"Main entry point: validate, merge, generate, and save.\"\"\"\n23:         self._validate_workspace_structure(workspace_path)\n24: \n25:         opts = MetadataOptions.from_options(options)\n26:         options_dict = asdict(opts)\n27: \n28:         metadata = self._load_or_create_metadata(workspace_path, options_dict)\n29:         metadata = self._apply_option_overrides(metadata, options_dict)\n30: \n31:         if not metadata.entrypoint:\n32:             metadata.entrypoint = self._infer_entrypoint(workspace_path, metadata.language)\n33: \n34:         self._validate_language_compatibility(workspace_path, metadata)\n35:         self._process_dependencies(workspace_path, metadata)\n36:         dockerfile_path = self._generate_dockerfile(workspace_path, metadata)\n37:         self._update_pack_metadata(workspace_path, metadata, dockerfile_path)\n38:         final_workspace = self._prepare_output_path(workspace_path, options.get(\"output\"))\n39: \n40:         return {\n41:             \"agent_name\": metadata.agent_name,\n42:             \"workspace_path\": str(workspace_path),\n43:             \"metadata_path\": str(workspace_path / \"agent_metadata.yaml\"),\n44:             \"dockerfile_path\": str(dockerfile_path) if dockerfile_path else None,\n45:             \"output_path\": str(final_workspace),\n46:         }\n47: \n48:     def _validate_workspace_structure(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None:\n49:         \"\"\"Validate that the workspace path exists and is a directory.\"\"\"\n50:         if not workspace_path.exists():\n51:             raise ValueError(f\"Workspace path does not exist: {workspace_path}\")\n52:         if not workspace_path.is_dir():\n53:             raise ValueError(f\"Workspace path is not a directory: {workspace_path}\")\n54: \n55:     def _load_or_create_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata:\n56:         \"\"\"Load existing metadata or create new from options.\"\"\"\n57:         metadata = self.metadata_service.load_metadata(workspace_path)\n58:         if metadata is not None:\n59:             return metadata\n60: \n61:         agent_name = options.get(\"agent_name\") or workspace_path.name\n62:         return AgentMetadata(\n63:             agent_name=agent_name,\n64:             language=options.get(\"language\") or \"python\",\n65:             entrypoint=options.get(\"entrypoint\") or \"\",\n66:             port=options.get(\"port\") or 8080,\n67:             build_mode=options.get(\"build_mode\") or \"local\",\n68:             description=options.get(\"description\"),\n69:             requirements_file=options.get(\"requirements_file\"),\n70:         )\n71: \n72:     def _apply_option_overrides(self, metadata: AgentMetadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata:\n73:         \"\"\"Apply CLI option overrides to existing metadata.\"\"\"\n74:         updates: Dict[str, Any] = {}\n75:         override_keys = [\n76:             \"agent_name\", \"language\", \"entrypoint\", \"port\", \"build_mode\",\n77:             \"description\", \"region\", \"workload_manager_url\", \"router_url\",\n78:             \"readiness_probe_path\", \"readiness_probe_port\",\n79:             \"registry_url\", \"registry_username\", \"registry_password\", \"agent_endpoint\",\n80:         ]\n81:         for key in override_keys:\n82:             value = options.get(key)\n83:             if value is not None and value != \"\":\n84:                 updates[key] = value\n85: \n86:         if updates:\n87:             metadata = metadata.model_copy(update=updates)\n88: \n89:         return metadata\n90: \n91:     def _validate_language_compatibility(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None:\n92:         \"\"\"Dispatch to language-specific validation.\"\"\"\n93:         if metadata.language == \"python\":\n94:             self._validate_python_compatibility(workspace_path)\n95:         elif metadata.language == \"java\":\n96:             self._validate_java_compatibility(workspace_path)\n97:         else:\n98:             raise ValueError(f\"Unsupported language: {metadata.language}\")\n99: \n100:     def _validate_python_compatibility(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None:\n101:         \"\"\"Validate Python workspace has at least one .py file.\"\"\"\n102:         py_files = list(workspace_path.glob(\"*.py\"))\n103:         if not py_files:\n104:             raise ValueError(\"No Python files found in workspace\")\n105: \n106:     def _validate_java_compatibility(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None:\n107:         \"\"\"Validate Java workspace has a valid pom.xml.\"\"\"\n108:         pom = workspace_path / \"pom.xml\"\n109:         if not pom.exists():\n110:             raise ValueError(\"pom.xml is required for Java projects\")\n111:         try:\n112:             ET.parse(str(pom))\n113:         except ET.ParseError:\n114:             raise ValueError(\"Invalid pom.xml: not valid XML\")\n115: \n116:     def _process_dependencies(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None:\n117:         \"\"\"Dispatch to language-specific dependency processing.\"\"\"\n118:         if metadata.language == \"python\":\n119:             self._process_python_dependencies(workspace_path, metadata)\n120:         elif metadata.language == \"java\":\n121:             self._process_java_dependencies(workspace_path)\n122: \n123:     def _process_python_dependencies(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None:\n124:         \"\"\"Validate Python requirements file.\"\"\"\n125:         req_file = metadata.requirements_file or \"requirements.txt\"\n126:         req_path = workspace_path / req_file\n127:         if req_path.exists():\n128:             content = req_path.read_text()\n129:             for line in content.splitlines():\n130:                 line = line.strip()\n131:                 if line and not line.startswith(\"#\") and not line.startswith(\"-\"):\n132:                     pass\n133: \n134:     def _process_java_dependencies(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None:\n135:         \"\"\"Validate Java pom.xml has dependencies section.\"\"\"\n136:         pom = workspace_path / \"pom.xml\"\n137:         try:\n138:             tree = ET.parse(str(pom))\n139:             root = tree.getroot()\n140:             ns = \"\"\n141:             if root.tag.startswith(\"{\"):\n142:                 ns = root.tag.split(\"}\")[0] + \"}\"\n143:             deps = root.find(f\"{ns}dependencies\")\n144:             if deps is None:\n145:                 pass\n146:         except ET.ParseError:\n147:             pass\n148: \n149:     def _generate_dockerfile(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> Optional[Path]:\n150:         \"\"\"Generate a Dockerfile if one doesn't already exist.\"\"\"\n151:         dockerfile = workspace_path / \"Dockerfile\"\n152:         if dockerfile.exists():\n153:             return dockerfile\n154: \n155:         if metadata.language == \"python\":\n156:             content = self._generate_python_dockerfile(metadata)\n157:         elif metadata.language == \"java\":\n158:             content = self._generate_java_dockerfile(metadata)\n159:         else:\n160:             return None\n161: \n162:         dockerfile.write_text(content)\n163:         return dockerfile\n164: \n165:     def _generate_python_dockerfile(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> str:\n166:         \"\"\"Generate a Python Dockerfile.\"\"\"\n167:         req_file = metadata.requirements_file or \"requirements.txt\"\n168:         entrypoint_parts = metadata.entrypoint.split()\n169:         cmd_json = json_array(entrypoint_parts)\n170:         return (\n171:             f\"FROM python:3.10-slim\\n\"\n172:             f\"WORKDIR /app\\n\"\n173:             f\"COPY {req_file} .\\n\"\n174:             f\"RUN pip install --no-cache-dir -r {req_file}\\n\"\n175:             f\"COPY . .\\n\"\n176:             f\"EXPOSE {metadata.port}\\n\"\n177:             f\"CMD {cmd_json}\\n\"\n178:         )\n179: \n180:     def _generate_java_dockerfile(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> str:\n181:         \"\"\"Generate a Java multi-stage Dockerfile.\"\"\"\n182:         entrypoint_parts = metadata.entrypoint.split()\n183:         cmd_json = json_array(entrypoint_parts)\n184:         return (\n185:             \"FROM maven:3.9-eclipse-temurin-17 AS build\\n\"\n186:             \"WORKDIR /app\\n\"\n187:             \"COPY pom.xml .\\n\"\n188:             \"RUN mvn package -DskipTests\\n\"\n189:             \"\\n\"\n190:             \"FROM eclipse-temurin:17-jre\\n\"\n191:             \"WORKDIR /app\\n\"\n192:             \"COPY --from=build /app/target/*.jar app.jar\\n\"\n193:             f\"EXPOSE {metadata.port}\\n\"\n194:             f\"CMD {cmd_json}\\n\"\n195:         )\n196: \n197:     def _update_pack_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata, dockerfile_path: Optional[Path]) -> None:\n198:         \"\"\"Save final metadata to agent_metadata.yaml.\"\"\"\n199:         if dockerfile_path is not None:\n200:             metadata = metadata.model_copy(update={\n201:                 \"image\": {\"dockerfile\": str(dockerfile_path)},\n202:             })\n203:         self.metadata_service.save_metadata(workspace_path, metadata)\n204: \n205:     def _prepare_output_path(self, workspace_path: Path, output_path: Optional[str]) -> Path:\n206:         \"\"\"Resolve the output path, creating directories if needed.\"\"\"\n207:         if output_path:\n208:             out = Path(output_path).resolve()\n209:             out.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n210:             return out\n211:         return workspace_path\n212: \n213:     def _infer_entrypoint(self, workspace_path: Path, language: str) -> str:\n214:         \"\"\"Infer the entrypoint command from workspace contents.\"\"\"\n215:         if language == \"python\":\n216:             py_files = sorted(workspace_path.glob(\"*.py\"))\n217:             if py_files:\n218:                 return f\"python {py_files[0].name}\"\n219:             raise ValueError(\"No Python files found in workspace. Provide --entrypoint explicitly.\")\n220:         elif language == \"java\":\n221:             return \"java -jar target/*.jar\"\n222:         raise ValueError(f\"Cannot infer entrypoint for language: {language}\")\n223: \n224: \n225: def json_array(parts: list[str]) -> str:\n226:     \"\"\"Format a list of strings as a JSON array string.\"\"\"\n227:     quoted = [f'\"{p}\"' for p in parts]\n228:     return \"[\" + \", \".join(quoted) + \"]\"\n\n(End of file - total 228 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"\"\"\"PackRuntime - orchestrates the agent workspace packaging lifecycle.\"\"\"\n\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nimport xml.etree.ElementTree as ET\nfrom dataclasses import asdict\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import Any, Dict, Optional\n\nfrom agentcube.models.pack_models import MetadataOptions\nfrom agentcube.services.metadata_service import AgentMetadata, MetadataService\n\n\nclass PackRuntime:\n    \"\"\"Orchestrates validation, metadata merging, and Dockerfile generation for an agent workspace.\"\"\"\n\n    def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None:\n        self.verbose = verbose\n        self.metadata_service = MetadataService(verbose=verbose)\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py","time":{"start":1775859513634,"end":1775859513642}}}}
