{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775859526548,"sessionID":"ses_28686b59affeAylUCxRXkYiV1W","part":{"id":"prt_d7979eb90001fZQS07kFssf3JM","messageID":"msg_d7979e3c1001kE9uQn9EFzFFfQ","sessionID":"ses_28686b59affeAylUCxRXkYiV1W","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775859664508,"sessionID":"ses_28686b59affeAylUCxRXkYiV1W","part":{"id":"prt_d7979fa94001bmqBk61nkargTf","messageID":"msg_d7979e3c1001kE9uQn9EFzFFfQ","sessionID":"ses_28686b59affeAylUCxRXkYiV1W","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_039747ca39c44e179db28b38","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-025 — MetadataService 与数据模型 — Design\n\n## Overview\n\nThis design specifies the full technical implementation of the metadata service layer and core data models for the AgentCube CLI. It covers three components:\n\n1. **`AgentMetadata`** — Pydantic `BaseModel` with 22 fields, 3 validators (`language`, `build_mode`, `port`), and `model_dump(exclude_none=True)` for YAML serialization.\n2. **`MetadataOptions`** — dataclass with 14 optional fields and a `from_options()` classmethod for CLI-to-model conversion.\n3. **`MetadataService`** — service class providing `load_metadata()`, `save_metadata()`, `update_metadata()`, `validate_workspace()`, and language-specific workspace validation.\n\nThese components form the foundation for all CLI lifecycle commands (`pack`, `build`, `publish`, `invoke`, `status`) — each Runtime class reads/writes workspace metadata through `MetadataService` rather than direct file I/O.\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\n### 2.1 Data Flow\n\n```\n┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                        CLI Commands (Typer)                           │\n│   pack / build / publish / invoke / status                            │\n└────────────────────────────┬─────────────────────────────────────────┘\n                             │\n          ┌──────────────────┴──────────────────┐\n          ▼                                     ▼\n┌─────────────────────┐             ┌─────────────────────┐\n│    Runtime Class    │             │   MetadataOptions   │\n│  (PackRuntime etc)  │             │   (CLI → dataclass) │\n│                     │             └──────────┬──────────┘\n│ .pack() / .build()  │                        │\n│ .publish() / etc    │                        ▼\n│                     │             ┌─────────────────────┐\n│  ├─ MetadataService │◄────────────│  asdict(opts)       │\n│  │   .load_metadata()             │  merge into updates  │\n│  │   .save_metadata()             └─────────────────────┘\n│  │   .update_metadata()\n│  │   .validate_workspace()        ┌─────────────────────┐\n│  └─ Business logic                │   AgentMetadata     │\n│     (Dockerfile, build, etc)      │   (Pydantic model)  │\n└─────────────────────┘             └──────────┬──────────┘\n                                               │\n                              ┌────────────────┴────────────────┐\n                              ▼                                 ▼\n                    ┌──────────────────┐            ┌──────────────────┐\n                    │  YAML file I/O   │            │  Validation      │\n                    │  agent_metadata. │            │  language:       │\n                    │    yaml ←→       │            │  build_mode:     │\n                    │  AgentMetadata   │            │  port: 1-65535   │\n                    └──────────────────┘            └──────────────────┘\n```\n\n### 2.2 Package Layout\n\n```\ncmd/cli/\n├── pyproject.toml                         — Dependencies (pydantic, pyyaml already declared)\n├── agentcube/\n│   ├── __init__.py                        — __version__, exports (no MetadataService/AgentMetadata)\n│   ├── cli/\n│   │   ├── __init__.py                    — Subpackage marker\n│   │   └── main.py                        — Typer app, commands, _handle_error\n│   ├── models/\n│   │   ├── __init__.py                    — Subpackage marker\n│   │   └── pack_models.py                 — MetadataOptions dataclass (EXISTING)\n│   ├── runtime/\n│   │   ├── __init__.py                    — Re-exports runtimes + MetadataOptions\n│   │   ├── pack_runtime.py                — PackRuntime (uses MetadataService)\n│   │   ├── build_runtime.py               — BuildRuntime (uses MetadataService)\n│   │   ├── publish_runtime.py             — PublishRuntime (uses MetadataService)\n│   │   ├── invoke_runtime.py              — InvokeRuntime (uses MetadataService)\n│   │   └── status_runtime.py              — StatusRuntime (uses MetadataService)\n│   ├── services/\n│   │   ├── __init__.py                    — Services package docstring\n│   │   ├── metadata_service.py            — AgentMetadata + MetadataService (EXISTING)\n│   │   ├── docker_service.py              — DockerService\n│   │   ├── k8s_provider.py                — KubernetesProvider\n│   │   └── agentcube_provider.py          — AgentCubeProvider\n│   └── operations/\n│       └── __init__.py                    — Placeholder module docstring\n└── tests/\n    ├── services/\n    │   ├── test_metadata_service.py       — MetadataService unit tests (EXISTING)\n    │   └── test_metadata_model.py         — AgentMetadata Pydantic tests (EXISTING)\n    └── models/\n        └── test_pack_models.py            — MetadataOptions tests (EXISTING)\n```\n\n### 2.3 Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Version | Purpose | Status |\n|------------|---------|---------|--------|\n| `pydantic` | `>=2.0.0` | `AgentMetadata` model definition, `field_validator`, `model_dump`, `model_copy` | Already declared |\n| `pyyaml` | `>=6.0` | `yaml.safe_load()`, `yaml.dump()` for metadata file I/O | Already declared |\n| `dataclasses` | stdlib | `MetadataOptions` dataclass, `asdict()` | stdlib, no install needed |\n| `pathlib` | stdlib | `Path` for workspace path handling | stdlib, no install needed |\n\nNo new dependencies are introduced.\n\n---\n\n## Component Design\n\n### 3.1 AgentMetadata (`agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`)\n\n```python\nclass AgentMetadata(BaseModel):\n    \"\"\"Pydantic model representing agent metadata.\"\"\"\n\n    agent_name: str = Field(..., description=\"Unique name identifying the agent\")\n    description: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Human-readable summary\")\n    language: str = Field(\"python\", description=\"Programming language used\")\n    entrypoint: str = Field(..., description=\"Command to launch the agent\")\n    port: int = Field(8080, description=\"Port exposed by the agent runtime\")\n    build_mode: str = Field(\"local\", description=\"Build strategy: local or cloud\")\n    region: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Deployment region\")\n    version: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Semantic version string for publishing\")\n    image: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = Field(None, description=\"Container image information\")\n    auth: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = Field(None, description=\"Authentication configuration\")\n    requirements_file: Optional[str] = Field(\"requirements.txt\", description=\"Python dependency file\")\n    registry_url: Optional[str] = Field(\"\", description=\"Registry URL for image publishing\")\n    registry_username: Optional[str] = Field(\"\", description=\"Registry username\")\n    registry_password: Optional[str] = Field(\"\", description=\"Registry password\")\n    agent_endpoint: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Agent endpoint URL\")\n    workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"URL for the Workload Manager\")\n    router_url: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"URL for the Router\")\n    readiness_probe_path: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Path for the readiness probe\")\n    readiness_probe_port: Optional[int] = Field(None, description=\"Port for the readiness probe\")\n    agent_id: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"Agent ID assigned by AgentCube\")\n    session_id: Optional[str] = Field(None, description=\"The session ID for the agent\")\n    k8s_deployment: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = Field(None, description=\"Kubernetes deployment information\")\n```\n\n#### 3.1.1 Field Categories\n\n| Category | Fields | Notes |\n|----------|--------|-------|\n| **Required** | `agent_name`, `entrypoint` | Must be provided at construction; no defaults |\n| **Validated enums** | `language`, `build_mode` | Normalized to lowercase; restricted to allowed values |\n| **Validated range** | `port` | Must be in `1..65535` |\n| **String defaults** | `requirements_file`, `registry_url`, `registry_username`, `registry_password` | Non-empty string defaults for operational fields |\n| **Optional (None)** | `description`, `region`, `version`, `image`, `auth`, `agent_endpoint`, `workload_manager_url`, `router_url`, `readiness_probe_path`, `readiness_probe_port`, `agent_id`, `session_id`, `k8s_deployment` | Excluded from YAML output when `None` |\n\n#### 3.1.2 Validators\n\n```python\n@field_validator(\"language\", mode=\"before\")\n@classmethod\ndef validate_language(cls, v: Optional[str]) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Normalize to lowercase; accept only 'python' or 'java'.\"\"\"\n    if v is None:\n        return \"python\"\n    lowered = v.lower()\n    if lowered not in (\"python\", \"java\"):\n        raise ValueError(f\"Unsupported language: {v}. Must be 'python' or 'java'.\")\n    return lowered\n\n@field_validator(\"build_mode\", mode=\"before\")\n@classmethod\ndef validate_build_mode(cls, v: Optional[str]) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Normalize to lowercase; accept only 'local' or 'cloud'.\"\"\"\n    if v is None:\n        return \"local\"\n    lowered = v.lower()\n    if lowered not in (\"local\", \"cloud\"):\n        raise ValueError(f\"Unsupported build_mode: {v}. Must be 'local' or 'cloud'.\")\n    return lowered\n\n@field_validator(\"port\")\n@classmethod\ndef validate_port(cls, v: int) -> int:\n    \"\"\"Validate port is within valid TCP range.\"\"\"\n    if v < 1 or v > 65535:\n        raise ValueError(f\"Port must be between 1 and 65535, got {v}\")\n    return v\n```\n\n**Design decisions:**\n- `mode=\"before\"` on `language` and `build_mode` validators ensures normalization happens before Pydantic's type coercion, allowing `None` → default mapping.\n- `port` validator uses default mode (after type coercion) since the field is already `int`.\n\n#### 3.1.3 Serialization\n\n```python\n# To dict for YAML — excludes None fields to keep output clean\ndata = metadata.model_dump(exclude_none=True)\n\n# To create a modified copy (used by update_metadata and callers)\nupdated = metadata.model_copy(update={\"port\": 9090, \"description\": \"new\"})\n```\n\n### 3.2 MetadataOptions (`agentcube/models/pack_models.py`)\n\n```python\n@dataclass\nclass MetadataOptions:\n    \"\"\"CLI options that map to AgentMetadata fields.\"\"\"\n\n    agent_name: Optional[str] = None\n    language: Optional[str] = \"python\"\n    entrypoint: Optional[str] = None\n    port: Optional[int] = 8080\n    build_mode: Optional[str] = \"local\"\n    requirements_file: Optional[str] = None\n    description: Optional[str] = None\n    workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = \"\"\n    router_url: Optional[str] = \"\"\n    readiness_probe_path: Optional[str] = \"\"\n    readiness_probe_port: Optional[int] = 8080\n    registry_url: Optional[str] = \"\"\n    registry_username: Optional[str] = \"\"\n    registry_password: Optional[str] = \"\"\n    agent_endpoint: Optional[str] = \"\"\n```\n\n#### 3.2.1 `from_options()` classmethod\n\n```python\n@classmethod\ndef from_options(cls, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> \"MetadataOptions\":\n    \"\"\"Create a MetadataOptions instance from a dict of CLI options.\n\n    Unknown fields are silently ignored. This allows callers to pass\n    the full **options dict from Typer commands without filtering.\n    \"\"\"\n    known_fields = {\n        \"agent_name\", \"language\", \"entrypoint\", \"port\", \"build_mode\",\n        \"requirements_file\", \"description\", \"workload_manager_url\",\n        \"router_url\", \"readiness_probe_path\", \"readiness_probe_port\",\n        \"registry_url\", \"registry_username\", \"registry_password\", \"agent_endpoint\",\n    }\n    filtered = {k: v for k, v in options.items() if k in known_fields}\n    return cls(**filtered)\n```\n\n**Design decisions:**\n- All fields are `Optional` so that `None` values can be distinguished from explicit defaults during merge logic.\n- String fields use `\"\"` as default (not `None`) for URL/path-type fields that should never be `None` in operational contexts.\n- `from_options()` silently ignores unknown keys — this is intentional to allow `**options` passthrough from Typer commands which may include `verbose`, `output`, etc.\n\n#### 3.2.2 Usage in PackRuntime\n\n```python\n# In PackRuntime.pack():\nopts = MetadataOptions.from_options(options)\noptions_dict = asdict(opts)\n\nmetadata = self._load_or_create_metadata(workspace_path, options_dict)\nmetadata = self._apply_option_overrides(metadata, options_dict)\n```\n\n### 3.3 MetadataService (`agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`)\n\n```python\nclass MetadataService:\n    \"\"\"Service for loading, saving, and updating agent metadata files.\"\"\"\n\n    METADATA_FILES: List[str] = [\"agent_metadata.yaml\", \"agent.yaml\", \"metadata.yaml\"]\n\n    def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None:\n        self.verbose = verbose\n```\n\n#### 3.3.1 `load_metadata(workspace_path: Path) -> Optional[AgentMetadata]`\n\n```python\ndef load_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path) -> Optional[AgentMetadata]:\n    \"\"\"Load agent metadata from the workspace directory.\n\n    Tries files in order: agent_metadata.yaml → agent.yaml → metadata.yaml.\n    Returns None if no metadata file exists.\n\n    Raises:\n        yaml.YAMLError: If the found file contains malformed YAML.\n        ValidationError: If the YAML content fails Pydantic validation.\n    \"\"\"\n    for filename in self.METADATA_FILES:\n        filepath = workspace_path / filename\n        if filepath.exists():\n            with open(filepath, \"r\") as f:\n                data = yaml.safe_load(f)\n            if data is None:\n                data = {}\n            return AgentMetadata(**data)\n    return None\n```\n\n**Key behaviors:**\n- Returns `None` (not a default `AgentMetadata`) when no file exists — callers must decide whether to create defaults.\n- Handles empty YAML files (`yaml.safe_load` returns `None`) by treating as empty dict.\n- Does **not** catch `yaml.YAMLError` or `ValidationError` — these propagate to callers for appropriate error handling.\n\n#### 3.3.2 `save_metadata(workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None`\n\n```python\ndef save_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None:\n    \"\"\"Save agent metadata to agent_metadata.yaml in the workspace directory.\n\n    Uses yaml.dump with:\n    - default_flow_style=False (block style, human-readable)\n    - indent=2 (2-space indentation)\n    - sort_keys=False (preserves model field definition order)\n    - model_dump(exclude_none=True) (omits None fields from output)\n    \"\"\"\n    filepath = workspace_path / \"agent_metadata.yaml\"\n    data = metadata.model_dump(exclude_none=True)\n    with open(filepath, \"w\") as f:\n        yaml.dump(data, f, default_flow_style=False, indent=2, sort_keys=False)\n```\n\n**Key behaviors:**\n- Always writes to `agent_metadata.yaml` (the canonical filename), regardless of which file was loaded.\n- Overwrites existing file without backup.\n- `exclude_none=True` ensures clean YAML output without `field: null` entries.\n\n#### 3.3.3 `update_metadata(workspace_path: Path, updates: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata`\n\n```python\ndef update_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, updates: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata:\n    \"\"\"Load existing metadata (or create default), apply updates, save, and return.\n\n    If no metadata file exists, creates a new AgentMetadata using the provided\n    updates for required fields (agent_name, entrypoint) and defaults for the rest.\n\n    Raises:\n        ValidationError: If the merged data fails Pydantic validation.\n    \"\"\"\n    existing = self.load_metadata(workspace_path)\n    if existing is None:\n        existing = AgentMetadata(\n            agent_name=updates.get(\"agent_name\", workspace_path.name),\n            entrypoint=updates.get(\"entrypoint\", \"\"),\n            language=updates.get(\"language\", \"python\"),\n            port=updates.get(\"port\", 8080),\n            build_mode=updates.get(\"build_mode\", \"local\"),\n        )\n    merged = existing.model_copy(update=updates)\n    self.save_metadata(workspace_path, merged)\n    return merged\n```\n\n**Key behaviors:**\n- Uses `model_copy(update=...)` for immutable merge — Pydantic validates the result.\n- When creating defaults, uses `workspace_path.name` as fallback for `agent_name`.\n- Validation errors from `model_copy()` propagate to callers.\n\n#### 3.3.4 `validate_workspace(workspace_path: Path) -> bool`\n\n```python\ndef validate_workspace(self, workspace_path: Path) -> bool:\n    \"\"\"Check if the workspace has valid metadata.\n\n    Returns True if any metadata file exists and can be loaded, False otherwise.\n    Note: This does NOT validate filesystem structure — only metadata file presence.\n    \"\"\"\n    return self.load_metadata(workspace_path) is not None\n```\n\n**Design note:** This method checks metadata file existence, not filesystem validity. Language-specific workspace validation (`.py` files, `pom.xml`) is handled by `_validate_python_workspace` and `_validate_java_workspace`.\n\n#### 3.3.5 `_validate_python_workspace(workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None`\n\n```python\ndef _validate_python_workspace(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None:\n    \"\"\"Validate a Python workspace has required files.\n\n    Requires:\n    - At least one *.py file in the workspace root\n    - The requirements file (from metadata.requirements_file or default \"requirements.txt\")\n    \"\"\"\n    py_files = list(workspace_path.glob(\"*.py\"))\n    if not py_files:\n        raise ValueError(\"No Python files found in workspace\")\n    req_file = metadata.requirements_file or \"requirements.txt\"\n    req_path = workspace_path / req_file\n    if not req_path.exists():\n        raise ValueError(f\"Dependency file not found: {req_file}\")\n```\n\n#### 3.3.6 `_validate_java_workspace(workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None`\n\n```python\ndef _validate_java_workspace(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None:\n    \"\"\"Validate a Java workspace has required files.\n\n    Requires:\n    - pom.xml in the workspace root\n    \"\"\"\n    pom = workspace_path / \"pom.xml\"\n    if not pom.exists():\n        raise ValueError(\"pom.xml is required for Java projects\")\n```\n\n**Note:** `MetadataService` validates presence of `pom.xml` but does not parse XML. `PackRuntime._validate_java_compatibility()` additionally parses `pom.xml` with `xml.etree.ElementTree` to verify well-formedness.\n\n---\n\n## Data Flow Details\n\n### 4.1 Pack Command Metadata Flow\n\n```\nCLI pack(workspace, agent_name, language, entrypoint, port, ...)\n  │\n  ├── PackRuntime.pack(workspace_path, **options)\n  │     │\n  │     ├── _validate_workspace_structure(workspace_path)\n  │     │     └── check path exists and is directory\n  │     │\n  │     ├── MetadataOptions.from_options(options) → opts\n  │     │     └── asdict(opts) → options_dict\n  │     │\n  │     ├── _load_or_create_metadata(workspace_path, options_dict)\n  │     │     ├── MetadataService.load_metadata() → existing or None\n  │     │     └── if None: create AgentMetadata from options_dict\n  │     │\n  │     ├── _apply_option_overrides(metadata, options_dict)\n  │     │     └── metadata.model_copy(update={non-None, non-empty values})\n  │     │\n  │     ├── infer entrypoint if missing\n  │     │\n  │     ├── _validate_language_compatibility(workspace_path, metadata)\n  │     │     ├── python → _validate_python_compatibility()\n  │     │     │     └── check *.py files exist\n  │     │     └── java → _validate_java_compatibility()\n  │     │           └── check pom.xml exists and is valid XML\n  │     │\n  │     ├── _process_dependencies(workspace_path, metadata)\n  │     │\n  │     ├── _generate_dockerfile(workspace_path, metadata)\n  │     │     └── generate Python or Java Dockerfile if none exists\n  │     │\n  │     ├── _update_pack_metadata(workspace_path, metadata, dockerfile_path)\n  │     │     └── MetadataService.save_metadata(workspace_path, metadata)\n  │     │\n  │     └── _prepare_output_path(workspace_path, output)\n  │\n  └── Return: {agent_name, workspace_path, metadata_path, dockerfile_path, output_path}\n```\n\n### 4.2 Build/Publish/Invoke/Status Metadata Flow\n\n```\nCLI build/publish/invoke/status(workspace, ...)\n  │\n  └── Runtime.build/publish/invoke/get_status(workspace_path, ...)\n        │\n        ├── MetadataService.load_metadata(workspace_path)\n        │     └── AgentMetadata or None\n        │\n        ├── Business logic uses metadata fields:\n        │     ├── build:    metadata.version, metadata.build_mode, metadata.image\n        │     ├── publish:  metadata.agent_name, metadata.version, metadata.k8s_deployment\n        │     ├── invoke:   metadata.agent_id, metadata.agent_endpoint, metadata.session_id\n        │     └── status:   metadata.agent_id, metadata.k8s_deployment\n        │\n        └── MetadataService.save_metadata() or update_metadata() (if state changes)\n```\n\n### 4.3 YAML Serialization Format\n\n**Input (AgentMetadata instance):**\n```python\nAgentMetadata(\n    agent_name=\"hello-agent\",\n    description=\"A simple hello world agent\",\n    language=\"python\",\n    entrypoint=\"python main.py\",\n    port=8080,\n    build_mode=\"local\",\n    version=\"0.1.0\",\n    image={\"name\": \"hello-agent\", \"tag\": \"0.1.0\"},\n)\n```\n\n**Output (agent_metadata.yaml):**\n```yaml\nagent_name: hello-agent\ndescription: A simple hello world agent\nlanguage: python\nentrypoint: python main.py\nport: 8080\nbuild_mode: local\nversion: 0.1.0\nimage:\n  name: hello-agent\n  tag: 0.1.0\n```\n\nNote: `version` is serialized as `0.1.0` (float-like) by PyYAML. This is a known behavior; the value round-trips correctly as a string when loaded back because Pydantic coerces it.\n\n---\n\n## Error Handling\n\n### 5.1 Error Matrix\n\n| Scenario | Error Type | Message | Raised By |\n|----------|-----------|---------|-----------|\n| No metadata file found | Returns `None` | — | `load_metadata()` |\n| Malformed YAML | `yaml.YAMLError` | PyYAML's native error | `load_metadata()` |\n| Unsupported language | `ValidationError` | `\"Unsupported language: {v}. Must be 'python' or 'java'.\"` | `AgentMetadata.validate_language` |\n| Unsupported build mode | `ValidationError` | `\"Unsupported build_mode: {v}. Must be 'local' or 'cloud'.\"` | `AgentMetadata.validate_build_mode` |\n| Port out of range | `ValidationError` | `\"Port must be between 1 and 65535, got {v}\"` | `AgentMetadata.validate_port` |\n| Missing required field | `ValidationError` | Pydantic's native `\"Field required\"` | `AgentMetadata` construction |\n| No Python files | `ValueError` | `\"No Python files found in workspace\"` | `_validate_python_workspace()` |\n| Missing requirements file | `ValueError` | `\"Dependency file not found: {req_file}\"` | `_validate_python_workspace()` |\n| Missing pom.xml | `ValueError` | `\"pom.xml is required for Java projects\"` | `_validate_java_workspace()` |\n\n### 5.2 Error Propagation Strategy\n\n- **`MetadataService`** does not wrap errors — it lets `yaml.YAMLError`, `ValidationError`, and `ValueError` propagate to callers.\n- **Runtime classes** catch errors at their boundary and re-raise as `RuntimeError` or let them bubble to the CLI layer.\n- **CLI layer** uses `_handle_error(e, command_name, verbose)` to format errors with Rich markup and exit code 1.\n\n### 5.3 Verbose Logging\n\nThe `verbose` flag on `MetadataService` is stored but not actively used for logging in the current implementation. Future enhancement: add `logging.debug()` calls in `load_metadata`, `save_metadata`, and `update_metadata` when `self.verbose` is `True`.\n\n---\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### 6.1 Test Coverage Matrix\n\n#### AgentMetadata Tests (`tests/services/test_metadata_model.py`)\n\n| Test Class | Scenarios |\n|------------|-----------|\n| `TestAgentMetadataValidCreation` | Minimal required fields only; all fields provided |\n| `TestAgentMetadataValidateLanguage` | `python`/`java` accepted; `Python`/`Java` normalized; `nodejs`/`ruby` rejected |\n| `TestAgentMetadataValidateBuildMode` | `local`/`cloud` accepted; `LOCAL` normalized; `hybrid` rejected |\n| `TestAgentMetadataValidatePort` | `1`, `8080`, `65535` accepted; `0`, `70000` rejected |\n| `TestAgentMetadataModelDump` | `exclude_none=True` omits None fields; required/defaults present |\n\n#### MetadataOptions Tests (`tests/models/test_pack_models.py`)\n\n| Test Class | Scenarios |\n|------------|-----------|\n| `TestMetadataOptionsDefaults` | All 14 fields have expected defaults |\n| `TestMetadataOptionsFromOptions` | Full dict; partial dict; unknown fields ignored; empty dict |\n\n#### MetadataService Tests (`tests/services/test_metadata_service.py`)\n\n| Test Class | Scenarios |\n|------------|-----------|\n| `TestLoadMetadataPrimaryExists` | Loads from `agent_metadata.yaml` |\n| `TestLoadMetadataFirstFallback` | Falls back to `agent.yaml` |\n| `TestLoadMetadataSecondFallback` | Falls back to `metadata.yaml` |\n| `TestLoadMetadataNoneExist` | Returns `None` when no file exists |\n| `TestSaveMetadataRoundTrip` | Save then load produces same values |\n| `TestSaveMetadataExcludeNone` | No `null` values in YAML output |\n| `TestSaveMetadataFormat` | 2-space indent, no trailing whitespace |\n| `TestUpdateMetadataMerge` | Partial update preserves existing fields |\n| `TestUpdateMetadataCreateNew` | Creates new metadata when no file exists |\n\n### 6.2 Test Fixtures\n\n```python\n@pytest.fixture\ndef service() -> MetadataService:\n    return MetadataService()\n\n@pytest.fixture\ndef workspace_with_primary(tmp_path: Path) -> Path:\n    ws = tmp_path / \"ws-primary\"\n    ws.mkdir()\n    (ws / \"agent_metadata.yaml\").write_text(\n        \"agent_name: primary-agent\\nlanguage: python\\nentrypoint: python main.py\\nport: 8080\\nbuild_mode: local\\n\"\n    )\n    (ws / \"main.py\").write_text(\"print('hello')\\n\")\n    return ws\n\n@pytest.fixture\ndef workspace_with_fallback1(tmp_path: Path) -> Path:\n    ws = tmp_path / \"ws-fb1\"\n    ws.mkdir()\n    (ws / \"agent.yaml\").write_text(\n        \"agent_name: fallback1-agent\\nlanguage: java\\nentrypoint: java -jar app.jar\\nport: 9090\\nbuild_mode: cloud\\n\"\n    )\n    (ws / \"pom.xml\").write_text(\"<project></project>\\n\")\n    return ws\n\n@pytest.fixture\ndef workspace_with_fallback2(tmp_path: Path) -> Path:\n    ws = tmp_path / \"ws-fb2\"\n    ws.mkdir()\n    (ws / \"metadata.yaml\").write_text(\n        \"agent_name: fallback2-agent\\nlanguage: python\\nentrypoint: python app.py\\nport: 3000\\nbuild_mode: local\\n\"\n    )\n    (ws / \"app.py\").write_text(\"print('hi')\\n\")\n    return ws\n\n@pytest.fixture\ndef empty_workspace(tmp_path: Path) -> Path:\n    ws = tmp_path / \"ws-empty\"\n    ws.mkdir()\n    return ws\n```\n\n### 6.3 Mock Strategy\n\n- **Filesystem:** Use `pytest` `tmp_path` fixture for isolated, auto-cleaned temporary directories.\n- **MetadataService:** Real instance (lightweight, no external dependencies — only `yaml` and `pathlib`).\n- **AgentMetadata:** Real Pydantic model (validators are pure functions, no side effects).\n- **MetadataOptions:** Real dataclass (pure data transformation).\n\nNo mocking is needed for the core metadata layer — all components are pure functions or simple file I/O.\n\n### 6.4 Gate Requirements\n\n1. `pytest tests/services/test_metadata_service.py -v` — all pass\n2. `pytest tests/services/test_metadata_model.py -v` — all pass\n3. `pytest tests/models/test_pack_models.py -v` — all pass\n4. `ruff check agentcube/services/metadata_service.py agentcube/models/pack_models.py` — no violations\n5. `mypy agentcube/services/metadata_service.py agentcube/models/pack_models.py` — no type errors\n6. Round-trip test: save → load produces equivalent field values\n7. All three validators tested for both acceptance and rejection cases\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Notes\n\n1. **`AgentMetadata` location**: Defined in `metadata_service.py` (not a separate `metadata_models.py`) because the model is tightly coupled to the service — it is the service's primary input/output type. This matches the existing codebase pattern.\n\n2. **`model_copy(update=...)` vs manual merge**: Pydantic v2's `model_copy(update=...)` is preferred over manual dict merging because it preserves type safety and re-runs validators on updated fields.\n\n3. **`None` vs `\"\"` defaults in MetadataOptions**: URL-type fields (`workload_manager_url`, `router_url`, etc.) default to `\"\"` rather than `None` because downstream code (e.g., `PackRuntime._apply_option_overrides`) checks `value is not None and value != \"\"` to determine whether to apply an override. This allows CLI defaults to be distinguished from \"not provided.\"\n\n4. **YAML version serialization**: PyYAML serializes `\"0.1.0\"` as `0.1.0` (unquoted, parsed as float on load). Pydantic's `str` type coercion handles this on reload. If strict string preservation is needed in the future, a custom YAML representer could be added.\n\n5. **File fallback priority**: `agent_metadata.yaml` → `agent.yaml` → `metadata.yaml`. The primary file (`agent_metadata.yaml`) is always the write target, regardless of which file was loaded. This ensures gradual migration from legacy filenames.\n\n6. **`validate_workspace` naming**: Despite the name, `MetadataService.validate_workspace()` only checks for metadata file presence. Actual filesystem validation (`.py` files, `pom.xml`) is done by `_validate_python_workspace` and `_validate_java_workspace`, called from `PackRuntime._validate_language_compatibility()`.\n\n7. **No concurrent write protection**: As a single-user CLI tool, file locking is not implemented. If concurrent access becomes a concern, `fcntl.flock()` could be added to `save_metadata`.\n\n8. **`services/__init__.py` exports**: Currently the file contains only a docstring. `MetadataService` and `AgentMetadata` are imported directly from `agentcube.services.metadata_service` by consumers (e.g., `PackRuntime`). No re-exports are added in this AR.\n\n9. **`runtime/__init__.py` exports**: Re-exports `MetadataOptions` from `agentcube.models.pack_models` for convenience:\n   ```python\n   from agentcube.models.pack_models import MetadataOptions\n   __all__ = [\"PackRuntime\", \"BuildRuntime\", \"PublishRuntime\", \"InvokeRuntime\", \"StatusRuntime\", \"MetadataOptions\"]\n   ```\n\n10. **Integration with existing Runtime classes**: All Runtime classes already import and use `MetadataService` and `AgentMetadata` from their canonical locations. No import path changes are needed — this AR documents and solidifies the existing implementation.\n","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-025/design.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/cmd/cli/agentcube/services/metadata_service.py\">\nERROR [101:24] Arguments missing for parameters \"description\", \"region\", \"version\", \"image\", \"auth\", \"requirements_file\", \"registry_url\", \"registry_username\", \"registry_password\", \"agent_endpoint\", \"workload_manager_url\", \"router_url\", \"readiness_probe_path\", \"readiness_probe_port\", \"agent_id\", \"session_id\", \"k8s_deployment\"\n</diagnostics>\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime